WEBVTT

00:01:44.604 --> 00:01:47.523
<i>[ Boy ]</i>
<i>ROGER, DO YOU BELIEVE</i> <i>IN HEAVEN?</i>

00:01:47.524 --> 00:01:51.027
I GUESS.  THAT'S WHERE
THEY SAY MY MOM WENT.

00:01:51.027 --> 00:01:55.114
MAYBE THAT'S WHERE
MY DAD WENT. PROBABLY.

00:01:55.115 --> 00:01:59.202
HEY, MAYBE YOUR MOM
AND MY DAD ARE FRIENDS UP THERE.

00:01:59.786 --> 00:02:04.457
THAT COULD BE.
'CAUSE YOU'RE MY BEST FRIEND DOWN HERE.

00:02:04.457 --> 00:02:07.960
YOU'RE MY BEST FRIEND
TOO, J.P.

00:02:22.559 --> 00:02:26.646
ROGER, HOW COME MAGGIE'S HOUSE
IS CALLED A FOSTER HOME?

00:02:27.230 --> 00:02:29.565
I DON'T KNOW.
MAYBE THE FIRST PEOPLE WHO LET...

00:02:29.566 --> 00:02:31.901
OTHER PEOPLE'S KIDS
LIVE WITH THEM WERE NAMED "FOSTER."

00:02:31.901 --> 00:02:37.156
OH.  SO IF WE STAY THERE
A LONG TIME, DO WE GOTTA CHANGE OUR NAME TO FOSTER?

00:02:37.157 --> 00:02:39.492
NO WAY.
GOOD.

00:02:40.076 --> 00:02:42.411
BESIDES, WE'RE NOT GONNA
BE THERE A LONG TIME.

00:02:42.412 --> 00:02:46.499
REALLY?
YEAH, SOMETHIN' GOOD'S GONNA HAPPEN.

00:02:47.083 --> 00:02:51.754
[ J.P. ]
YEAH, SOMETHIN' GOOD.  MAYBE TODAY, EVEN.  IT COULD HAPPEN.

00:03:06.936 --> 00:03:09.271
[ Sportscaster ]
THE ANGELS, TRYING TO BREAK A 14-GAME LOSING STREAK,

00:03:09.272 --> 00:03:13.359
FACE THE TORONTO BLUE JAYS
HERE THIS AFTERNOON AT ANAHEIM STADIUM.

00:03:13.359 --> 00:03:15.110
MAGGIE, WE'RE BACK.

00:03:17.447 --> 00:03:19.198
SO, WHERE YA BEEN?

00:03:19.199 --> 00:03:23.286
JUST RIDIN' AROUND.
YOU SAID BE BACK BY 5:00.

00:03:26.789 --> 00:03:30.292
I CAN'T TELL TIME YET.
ARE WE BACK BY 5:00?

00:03:30.293 --> 00:03:34.380
CLOSE.  COME ON, J.P.,
GET YOUR BIKE IN.  ROGER?

00:03:34.380 --> 00:03:38.467
YEAH?
YOU HAVE A VISITOR. HE'S WAITING INSIDE FOR YOU.

00:03:38.468 --> 00:03:40.803
IS IT--

00:03:47.810 --> 00:03:50.729
DAD?
<i>HEY.</i>

00:03:50.730 --> 00:03:54.233
DAD.
SURPRISED TO SEE ME?

00:03:56.569 --> 00:03:58.904
YEAH.

00:03:58.905 --> 00:04:04.744
YOU LOOK KINDA SCRAWNY.
DON'T THEY FEED YOU ENOUGH IN THIS PLACE?

00:04:04.744 --> 00:04:06.495
YEAH.

00:04:06.496 --> 00:04:12.335
WHERE YOU BEEN?
I WAS WAITIN'. JUST RIDIN' AROUND THE STADIUM.

00:04:12.335 --> 00:04:14.670
- ANGELS STILL YOUR TEAM?
- YEAH.

00:04:14.671 --> 00:04:17.590
THEY'RE IN LAST PLACE.

00:04:19.342 --> 00:04:21.093
YEAH.

00:04:21.094 --> 00:04:24.013
RUNS IN THE BLOOD.

00:04:24.013 --> 00:04:26.932
<i>FAMILY THAT LIKES LOSERS.</i>

00:04:31.020 --> 00:04:34.523
SO...
I CAME TO SAY...

00:04:34.524 --> 00:04:36.859
THAT I'M GOIN'
UP NORTH.

00:04:37.443 --> 00:04:41.530
I KNOW I SAID
WHEN I CAME IT'D BE TO GET YOU, BUT...

00:04:41.531 --> 00:04:45.034
[ Sighs ]
THINGS AIN'T WORKIN' OUT THAT WAY.

00:04:51.457 --> 00:04:56.128
I DID WHAT I COULD WITH YA.
MAYBE IF YOUR MOM WAS ALIVE IT'D BE DIFFERENT.

00:04:57.880 --> 00:05:00.215
I, UH--  THEY HAD ME SIGN
THIS THING, THIS PAPER.

00:05:00.216 --> 00:05:05.471
SOME KIND OF RELEASE THING.
UH, JUST GOTTA GO TO COURT TO MAKE IT FINAL.

00:05:07.223 --> 00:05:11.310
YOU UNDERSTAND
WHAT I'M SAYIN', DON'T YA?

00:05:12.478 --> 00:05:14.813
Y-YEAH.

00:05:14.814 --> 00:05:17.733
OKAY, I'M GLAD WE GOT
THAT OUTTA THE WAY.

00:05:24.741 --> 00:05:26.492
WHERE'S THE PICKUP?

00:05:26.492 --> 00:05:30.579
I TRADED IT IN.
THE BIKE'S BETTER FOR TRAVELIN'.

00:05:32.332 --> 00:05:35.835
DAD, WHEN WE GONNA BE
A FAMILY AGAIN?

00:05:38.171 --> 00:05:40.506
FROM WHERE I'M SITTIN',

00:05:42.842 --> 00:05:46.345
I'D SAY WHEN THE ANGELS
WIN THE PENNANT.

00:05:46.346 --> 00:05:48.681
YOU STAY OUTTA
TROUBLE, SON.

00:05:48.681 --> 00:05:50.432
[ Motorcycle Starts, Revs ]

00:06:03.279 --> 00:06:05.030
[ Faint Crowd Cheering ]

00:06:05.031 --> 00:06:09.201
[ Stadium Announcer ]
NUMBER 27, SHORTSTOP, STEVE ACKER.

00:06:09.202 --> 00:06:12.705
[ Sportscaster ]  SO WITH THE
ANGELS DOWN BY SEVEN, IT'S NOW ONE BALL, TWO STRIKES TO ACKER,

00:06:12.705 --> 00:06:16.208
- <i>THE FORTH BATTER TO FACE</i>
<i>GATES HERE IN THE EIGHTH.</i> <i>- COME ON, STRIKE 'IM OUT!</i>

00:06:16.209 --> 00:06:17.960
YEAH!  STRIKE 'IM OUT!

00:06:17.960 --> 00:06:20.879
[ Sportscaster ]
...AND GOT GODCHAUX ON A POP-UP TO MITCHELL AT THIRD.

00:06:21.464 --> 00:06:23.799
BURN IT IN THERE.

00:06:23.800 --> 00:06:26.135
<i>[ Man ]</i>
<i>COME ON, ANGELS,</i> <i>LET'S STAY IN THIS.</i>

00:06:26.135 --> 00:06:28.470
[ Sportscaster ]
GATES TAKES THE SIGN,

00:06:29.055 --> 00:06:33.142
CHECKS THE RUNNER AT FIRST
AND DELIVERS.

00:06:33.142 --> 00:06:36.061
[ Crowd Groaning ]
ACKER LOBS THE BALL HIGH INTO LEFT FIELD.

00:06:36.062 --> 00:06:38.397
<i>[ Man ]</i>
<i>GATES, YOU STINK!</i>

00:06:38.398 --> 00:06:41.901
NORTON AND WILLIAMS
BOTH GOING FOR THE CATCH.

00:06:42.485 --> 00:06:44.820
I-I GOT IT.  I GOT IT.
AND THIS'LL BE BEN WILLIAMS' CALL.

00:06:47.156 --> 00:06:51.243
AND WILLIAMS AND NORTON COLLIDE
AND THE CATCH IS BLOWN!

00:06:51.244 --> 00:06:54.163
[ Crowd Booing ]
WHERE'S THE BALL? UUH!                   OOH!

00:06:54.163 --> 00:06:58.834
BOY, THEY'RE BAD!

00:06:58.835 --> 00:07:01.754
- OHH!
- [ Sportscaster ] AND WITH ANOTHER EXAMPLE...

00:07:01.754 --> 00:07:04.673
OF HIS INFAMOUS TEMPER,
MANAGER GEORGE KNOX CALLS TIME OUT.

00:07:04.674 --> 00:07:07.593
HE WILL HAVE A WORD
WITH HIS PITCHER, FRANK GATES.

00:07:07.593 --> 00:07:09.928
I DON'T THINK IT'S GONNA BE
A HAPPY WORD.

00:07:09.929 --> 00:07:12.848
[ Sportscaster ]
AND IT LOOKS LIKE KNOX IS GOING TO TAKE GATES OUT.

00:07:12.849 --> 00:07:16.936
GATES DOESN'T LOOK
TOO PLEASED ABOUT THIS.

00:07:16.936 --> 00:07:20.439
GIMME THE BALL.
IT AIN'T MY FAULT. YOU NEED A NEW OUTFIELD.

00:07:20.440 --> 00:07:22.191
YOU'RE OUTTA HERE!
GIVE ME THE BALL!

00:07:22.191 --> 00:07:25.694
YOU WANT THE BALL?
HERE YOU GO.  GO GET IT!

00:07:26.279 --> 00:07:28.614
- <i>GATES HAS THROWN HIS BALL</i>
<i>AND GLOVE INTO THE STANDS.</i> <i>- MY GLOVE?  GO GET IT!</i>

00:07:28.614 --> 00:07:31.533
GO ON, GET OUTTA HERE!
YOU'RE FINISHED, GATES!

00:07:31.534 --> 00:07:33.869
- <i>AND KNOX HAS ATTACKED</i>
<i>HIS OWN PITCHER!</i> <i>- UH-OH!</i>

00:07:33.870 --> 00:07:36.205
SKIP, SKIP.
LET 'EM GO, SKIP.

00:07:36.205 --> 00:07:40.292
YOU'RE WASHED UP!
YOU'LL NEVER PITCH AGAIN! YOU'RE CRAZY, KNOX!

00:07:40.293 --> 00:07:43.796
THEY'RE CLEARING THE BENCHES!
NOW BOTH TEAMS ARE ON THE FIELD!

00:07:43.796 --> 00:07:45.547
HEY!  IT'S NOT
OUR FIGHT!

00:07:46.132 --> 00:07:49.051
- <i>GEORGE KNOX HAS CREATED</i>
<i>TOTAL CHAOS!</i> <i>- [ Blue Jays ]  HUH?  WHAT?</i>

00:07:49.051 --> 00:07:51.970
HIT HIM ONE
FOR ME, GATES! I CAN'T FIND HIM!

00:07:51.971 --> 00:07:54.890
- YOU'RE CRAZY!
- YOU CAN'T MANAGE A TEAM!

00:07:54.891 --> 00:08:00.146
THIS IS OUTRAGEOUS!
GEORGE KNOX FIGHTING OFF HIS OWN PLAYERS,

00:08:00.146 --> 00:08:03.065
[ Sighs ]
SURPRISE, SURPRISE.

00:08:03.649 --> 00:08:05.984
AND THEY'RE TRYING TO KEEP
KNOX AND GATES APART.

00:08:05.985 --> 00:08:07.736
YOU STINK, KNOX!

00:08:07.737 --> 00:08:10.656
KNOX, YOU'RE OUTTA HERE!

00:08:10.656 --> 00:08:12.991
COME ON, UMP,
LEAVE 'IM IN.

00:08:12.992 --> 00:08:15.911
YEAH!
DON'T THROW 'IM OUT!

00:08:15.912 --> 00:08:18.831
- HEY!  WHAT ARE YOU KIDS
DOIN' UP THERE? - [ Gasps ]  UH-OH!

00:08:18.831 --> 00:08:20.582
YOU BETTER HAVE TICKETS
FOR THAT TREE!

00:08:20.583 --> 00:08:22.918
GAME'S OVER FOR US, J.P.
WE GOTTA GO!

00:08:22.919 --> 00:08:25.254
THAT'S RIGHT, CLEAR OFF!
GO ON, GET OUTTA HERE!

00:08:25.254 --> 00:08:28.757
YOU HEARD ME!
DON'T LET ME CATCH YOU TWERPS AROUND HERE AGAIN!

00:08:28.758 --> 00:08:31.093
YOU KICKIN' ME OUT?
THAT'S GOOD! YES, I'M KICKING YOU OUT!

00:08:31.093 --> 00:08:32.844
'CAUSE YOU BEEN STINKIN' UP
THE CALLS ALL DAY! YOU'RE GONE!

00:08:32.845 --> 00:08:36.348
[ Knox ]  YOU CAN'T
KICK ME OUT 'CAUSE I'M LEAVIN'. YOU GET THAT?  I'M OUTTA HERE!

00:08:36.349 --> 00:08:41.020
[ Sportscaster ]  AND KNOX WILL
WATCH THE REST OF THE GAME... IN THE LOCKER ROOM.

00:08:41.020 --> 00:08:45.691
MURPHY'S OUT OF HIS MIND
TO PUT UP WITH THIS NONSENSE.

00:08:45.691 --> 00:08:49.194
YOU THINK YOU
CAN DO ANY BETTER? [ Scoffs ]  BLINDFOLDED.

00:08:49.195 --> 00:08:52.114
WELL, WHEN YOU WERE MANAGING,
BOY, YOU HAD A LOT OF TROUBLE. I REMEMBER--

00:08:52.114 --> 00:08:55.617
[ Sizzling ]
ZIP IT, PAL.  YOU HAVE TO ASK YOURSELF, WHAT IS GOIN' ON...

00:08:55.618 --> 00:08:58.537
WITH THIS TEAM,
AND HOW LONG WILL OWNER HANK MURPHY PUT UP...

00:08:58.538 --> 00:09:00.873
WITH THIS KIND OF BEHAVIOR
FROM HIS MANAGER.

00:09:00.873 --> 00:09:04.960
I THOUGHT I'D SEEN IT ALL,
LADIES AND GENTLEMEN, BUT WITH GEORGE KNOX CALLING THE SHOTS,

00:09:05.545 --> 00:09:06.712
Q5
YOU NEVER KNOW WHAT WILL HAPPEN.

00:09:06.712 --> 00:09:09.047
CAREFUL, J.P.
LET'S GO!

00:09:16.055 --> 00:09:19.558
WHY DO YOU IDIOTS DO THAT
AFTER WE'VE LOST? IT'S FOR GOOD LUCK, MAN.

00:09:19.559 --> 00:09:22.478
AFTER FIFTEEN STRAIGHT
LOSSES, I SAY WE FIND SOMETHIN' ELSE TO RUB.

00:09:22.478 --> 00:09:25.397
LIKE TRISCUIT'S HEAD.
DON'T EVEN THINK ABOUT TOUCHIN' ME... ANYWHERE.

00:09:25.398 --> 00:09:28.317
FATTY PANTS.
MAYBE WE SHOULD DO THIS BEFORE WE LOSE.

00:09:28.317 --> 00:09:32.988
÷[
AW, NOT AGAIN!  THEY GOT THE WRONG KIND OF SALAMI!

00:09:32.989 --> 00:09:36.492
IT WAS NICE OF KNOX
TO LET YOU PLAY. HEY, I CAN HIT IT.  YOU GOTTA,

00:09:36.492 --> 00:09:39.411
YOU GOTTA CHOKE UP
AND BEAR DOWN, THEN YOU'LL GET YOUR HOMER.

00:09:41.163 --> 00:09:44.082
HEY, HOW'S THE ARM?
IT'S FEELIN' STRONG.

00:09:44.083 --> 00:09:47.002
YOU'LL BE PITCHIN' NO-HITTERS
ANY DAY NOW.

00:09:47.003 --> 00:09:50.506
♪ WE ARE THE BOYS OF SUMMER
AND IT'S A BIG BUMMER ♪

00:09:50.506 --> 00:09:53.425
♪ NO MATTER WHO WE PLAY
WE GIVE THE GAME AWAY ♪

00:09:53.426 --> 00:09:56.929
♪ 'CAUSE WE CAN'T WIN
THAT WOULD BE A SIN ♪

00:09:56.929 --> 00:10:01.600
♪ WE EVEN LOSE THE GAMES
BEFORE THEY BEGIN ♪ SAVE IT, MAPEL!

00:10:14.447 --> 00:10:16.782
- BUMMER.
- ONE MORE LOSS!

00:10:16.782 --> 00:10:20.285
ONE MORE LOSS
WHICH COULD HAVE BEEN A WIN!

00:10:20.286 --> 00:10:22.621
YOU CALL YOURSELVES
PROFESSIONALS.

00:10:22.622 --> 00:10:27.293
I HAVE NEVER, EVER SEEN
A WORSE GROUP OF 25 PLAYERS!

00:10:27.293 --> 00:10:33.132
YOU DON'T THINK AS A TEAM,
YOU DON'T PLAY AS A TEAM, YOU DON'T EVEN LOSE AS A TEAM!

00:10:33.132 --> 00:10:36.051
YOU ALL GOT YOUR HEADS
SO FAR UP YOUR BUTTS...

00:10:36.052 --> 00:10:39.555
YOU CAN'T EVEN SEE
THE LIGHT OF DAY!

00:10:39.555 --> 00:10:44.810
ONE MORE LOSS AND I'LL,
AND I'LL DO THIS--  AAH! TO EACH AND EVERY ONE OF YOU!

00:10:45.978 --> 00:10:47.729
HO-HO-HO!

00:10:48.314 --> 00:10:51.817
I WANT YOU HERE, IN UNIFORM,
AT 9:00 TOMORROW.

00:10:51.817 --> 00:10:54.736
WE'RE GOING BACK TO WORK
ON FUNDAMENTALS!

00:10:54.737 --> 00:10:56.488
FUNDAMENTALS?
IN THE MIDDLE OF THE SEASON?

00:10:56.489 --> 00:10:59.992
I THOUGHT THE GAME
STARTED AT 1:00.

00:10:59.992 --> 00:11:04.079
IT <i>DOES</i> START AT 1:00.
AND YOU'RE A JACKASS!

00:11:04.080 --> 00:11:05.831
- NO, I'M A PITCHER.
- [ Groaning ]

00:11:06.415 --> 00:11:09.334
I THINK YOU'RE A PITCHER
AND A JACKASS. <i>SI.</i>  IT'S VERY COMMON.

00:11:09.335 --> 00:11:11.086
OH.

00:11:18.094 --> 00:11:21.013
TOUGH LOSS, GEORGE.

00:11:21.597 --> 00:11:24.516
I CAN'T TAKE IT ANYMORE.
YOU HAVE TO START TRADING 'EM.

00:11:24.517 --> 00:11:26.852
ALL OF THEM, NOW.

00:11:26.852 --> 00:11:32.107
I CAN'T TRADE 25 PLAYERS.
I CAN'T WIN WITH THESE GUYS. NOBODY CAN.

00:11:32.108 --> 00:11:35.611
THERE'S A THING
CALLED TALENT. THEY DON'T HAVE IT.

00:11:35.611 --> 00:11:38.530
THIS ISN'T CINCINNATI,
GEORGE.

00:11:38.531 --> 00:11:41.450
NO ONE EXPECTS YOU
TO WIN BIG WITH THESE BOYS.

00:11:42.034 --> 00:11:46.121
I CAME HERE TO MANAGE
A WINNING BASEBALL TEAM.

00:11:46.122 --> 00:11:50.209
YOU JUST HANG ON, PARTNER.
YOU'LL RIDE THROUGH 'THE DARK DAYS.

00:11:50.793 --> 00:11:53.128
[ Man On Bullhorn ]
MR. KNOX, WE'RE WAITING ON THE FIELD.

00:11:53.129 --> 00:11:54.880
WE'RE WAITING.

00:11:57.216 --> 00:11:58.967
WHAT'S THAT?

00:11:58.968 --> 00:12:01.887
DAVID MONTAGNE,
ADMINISTRATIVE ASSISTANT FOR MEDIA RELATIONS.

00:12:01.887 --> 00:12:05.974
YOU'RE SCHEDULED TO DO
RANCH WILDER'S POSTGAME SHOW HERE, AND HE'S BEEN WAITING.

00:12:05.975 --> 00:12:08.310
THE PRESS ARE ALL SCUM.
THEY'RE MEANT TO BE KEPT WAITING.

00:12:08.310 --> 00:12:11.813
RANCH WILDER'S WORSE THAN SCUM.
WHO'S FAULT IS THAT? THAT IS NOT MY FAULT.

00:12:11.814 --> 00:12:14.733
WHAT EVER HAPPENED
TO BARNEY OR BAILEY, OR WHATEVER THE JERK'S NAME IS?

00:12:14.734 --> 00:12:17.653
YOU FIRED HIM
AND THEY HIRED ME ON MONDAY.

00:12:17.653 --> 00:12:22.324
THEN I CAN'T OFFICIALLY
FIRE YOU UNTIL FRIDAY. MAKE A NOTE.

00:12:24.076 --> 00:12:26.411
UH, WHERE,
WHERE, WHERE?

00:12:26.412 --> 00:12:28.163
ALL RIGHT, ALL RIGHT.

00:12:28.164 --> 00:12:30.499
MICROPHONE?

00:12:30.499 --> 00:12:34.002
THROWN OUT OF THE GAME.
I IMAGINE THE COMMISSIONER'S FINALLY HAPPY.

00:12:34.587 --> 00:12:36.338
WE'RE ON IN THREE,
TWO, ONE.

00:12:36.338 --> 00:12:41.009
AND WE'RE BACK WITH
ANGELS' MANAGER, GEORGE KNOX. THIS WAS A TOUGH LOSS TODAY.

00:12:41.010 --> 00:12:44.513
ANY LOSS IS HARD.
BUT THIS ONE REALLY GOT TO YOU.

00:12:45.097 --> 00:12:48.600
YOU LEAVE CINCINNATI AFTER
TEN YEARS OF WINNING BALL CLUBS, ALTHOUGH THE REALLY BIG ONE...

00:12:48.601 --> 00:12:52.104
ALWAYS SEEMED TO BE JUST
OUT OF REACH, AND YOU COME OUT HERE TO MANAGE OUR ANGELS.

00:12:52.104 --> 00:12:55.023
NOW, EXPECTATIONS WERE HIGH
THAT YOU COULD TURN THIS TEAM AROUND,

00:12:55.024 --> 00:12:58.527
BUT THAT JUST DOESN'T
SEEM TO BE HAPPENING.

00:12:58.527 --> 00:13:02.030
SEASON'S ONLY
HALF OVER, RANCH. AND YOUR CLUB'S IN LAST PLACE.

00:13:02.615 --> 00:13:05.534
YOU OUGHTA KNOW HOW ONE INCIDENT
CAN CHANGE THE COURSE OF EVENTS.

00:13:05.534 --> 00:13:07.869
WELL, YOU KNOW,
YOU PLAY THE GAME, YOU TAKE YOUR CHANCES.

00:13:07.870 --> 00:13:11.373
SOMETIMES YOU'RE JUST IN THE
WRONG PLACE AT THE WRONG TIME. YEAH, YOU'RE AN EXPERT AT THAT.

00:13:11.373 --> 00:13:16.044
I COULD SAY THE SAME ABOUT YOU.
WELL, ACTIONS SPEAK LOUDER THAN WORDS.

00:13:16.045 --> 00:13:17.796
WELL, THAT'LL WRAP THINGS UP
HERE IN THE FIELD-- HEY, I'M STILL ON THE AIR HERE.

00:13:17.797 --> 00:13:20.132
<i>OH, YEAH?</i>
<i>OOH!</i>

00:13:21.300 --> 00:13:25.387
WE'RE SPEAKING WITH
ANGELS' MANGER GEORGE KNOX. GEORGE? OH!

00:13:25.387 --> 00:13:27.138
AND, UH,
WE'LL BE RIGHT BACK.

00:13:27.139 --> 00:13:30.642
[ Maggie ]
OH, ROGER, YOU HAVEN'T EATEN A THING.

00:13:30.643 --> 00:13:33.562
<i>I'M NOT HUNGRY.</i>

00:13:33.562 --> 00:13:37.065
MIGUEL, YOU HAVE TO MISS
THE BASEBALL GAME TOMORROW.

00:13:37.066 --> 00:13:40.569
I'M SORRY,
YOUR SOCIAL WORKER CALLED AND YOU HAVE AN INTERVIEW.

00:13:40.569 --> 00:13:42.320
SHE'LL BE HERE AT 11:00.

00:13:42.905 --> 00:13:46.408
GOOD, I DON'T WANT TO GO
TO THE GAME ANYWAY. ANGELS NEVER WIN.

00:13:46.408 --> 00:13:51.663
[ Scoffs ]
I WANT TO GO TO THE GAME.  THEY COULD WIN.  IT COULD HAPPEN.

00:13:51.664 --> 00:13:54.583
YEAH, AND YOU COULD
DROP DEAD AFTER DINNER WITH FOOD POISONING.

00:13:54.583 --> 00:13:59.838
LEAVE 'IM ALONE!
BOYS!  HEY, LOOK WHAT WE'VE GOT FOR DESSERT.  JELL-O.

00:13:59.839 --> 00:14:02.758
- YEA!
- IT'S NOT REALLY JELL-O.

00:14:02.758 --> 00:14:05.677
IT'S CAT BRAINS
WITH FOOD COLORING. SHE KILLS 'EM AT NIGHT...

00:14:05.678 --> 00:14:08.013
- AND FEEDS 'EM TO US
TO SAVE MONEY. - SHUT UP, MIGUEL!

00:14:08.597 --> 00:14:12.684
ROGER, YOU KNOW WE DO NOT USE
THOSE WORDS IN THIS HOUSE.

00:14:12.685 --> 00:14:15.020
MEOW!

00:14:15.020 --> 00:14:19.691
AND YOU KNOW I WOULD NEVER USE
FOOD COLORING ON MY CAT BRAINS.

00:14:27.283 --> 00:14:30.786
OKAY, DID WE WASH OUR FACES?
YEAH?

00:14:30.786 --> 00:14:34.873
BRUSH OUR TEETH?
BEEN TO THE BATHROOM?

00:14:34.874 --> 00:14:38.961
DID YOU PICK THE LINT
FROM BETWEEN YOUR TOES? YEAH?

00:14:39.545 --> 00:14:42.464
DID YOU SAY YOUR PRAYERS?
<i>YEAH.</i> <i>YEAH.</i>

00:14:42.464 --> 00:14:44.799
OH, YEAH?  NIGHT.

00:14:44.800 --> 00:14:46.551
<i>NIGHT, MAGGIE.</i>
<i>GOOD NIGHT, MAGGIE.</i>

00:14:48.888 --> 00:14:51.223
- I DIDN'T SAY MY PRAYERS.
- I DIDN'T WASH MY FACE.

00:14:51.223 --> 00:14:54.142
- WHAT'S LINT, AGAIN?
- SHUT UP, BUTT-HEAD!

00:14:54.143 --> 00:14:59.398
WHY DO WE GOTTA SLEEP IN THESE
SLEEPING BAGS?  I HAVEN'T PEED THE BED IN A LONG TIME.

00:14:59.398 --> 00:15:01.149
[ Sighs ]
YOU PEED THE BED LAST WEEK.

00:15:01.150 --> 00:15:05.237
SHE MAKES US SLEEP IN
SLEEPING BAGS 'CAUSE SHE TOO OLD TO BEND OVER AND TUCK IN SHEETS.

00:15:05.237 --> 00:15:09.324
- SHE ISN'T TOO OLD.
SHE'S GOT A LOT TO DO. - DID YOU GUYS PRAY?

00:15:09.325 --> 00:15:13.996
I PRAY EVERY NIGHT YOU GO TO BED
WITHOUT BUGGIN' US WITH A THOUSAND STUPID QUESTIONS.

00:15:13.996 --> 00:15:17.499
MAYBE TOMORROW YOU'LL MEET
A NICE FAMILY, MIGUEL.

00:15:17.499 --> 00:15:21.586
<i>I'LL PRAY FOR THAT.</i>
<i>IT COULD HAPPEN.</i>

00:15:39.688 --> 00:15:42.607
[ Whispering ]
GOD--

00:15:42.608 --> 00:15:45.527
IF THERE IS A GOD--

00:15:45.527 --> 00:15:50.782
IF YOU'RE A MAN OR A WOMAN,
IF YOU'RE LISTENIN',

00:15:52.534 --> 00:15:55.453
I'D REALLY, REALLY LIKE...

00:15:56.038 --> 00:15:58.957
A FAMILY.

00:15:58.958 --> 00:16:04.797
MY DAD SAYS THAT'LL ONLY HAPPEN
IF THE ANGELS WIN THE PENNANT.

00:16:04.797 --> 00:16:07.716
THE BASEBALL TEAM,
I MEAN.

00:16:07.716 --> 00:16:10.635
SO, MAYBE YOU COULD
HELP 'EM WIN A LITTLE.

00:16:13.555 --> 00:16:15.890
AMEN.

00:16:20.562 --> 00:16:22.897
UH, A-WOMEN TOO.

00:16:31.073 --> 00:16:33.408
[ Knocking ]
COME IN.

00:16:33.409 --> 00:16:36.328
YOU WANTED TO SEE ME?

00:16:36.328 --> 00:16:40.415
YOU FEELIN' ANY BETTER
TODAY, GEORGE? WHY WOULD I BE FEELIN' BETTER?

00:16:40.416 --> 00:16:44.503
COMMISSIONER FINED YOU $5,000
FOR JUMPIN' GATES.

00:16:44.503 --> 00:16:48.006
<i>AND WORD HAS IT RANCH</i>
<i>IS PRESSIN' CIVIL CHARGES</i> <i>FOR YOU POPPIN' 'IM.</i>

00:16:48.590 --> 00:16:51.509
COME TO THINK OF IT,
I HAVE FELT BETTER SINCE I SLUGGED WILDER.

00:16:51.510 --> 00:16:54.429
- YOUR PISTOL'S SMOKIN', PAL.
- I HADN'T MADE THE CONNECTION.

00:16:54.430 --> 00:16:57.933
I KNOW YOU AND WILDER HAVE
BEEN AT EACH OTHER'S THROATS SINCE YOU WERE PLAYERS.

00:16:57.933 --> 00:17:02.020
YEAH, WE'VE BEEN AT EACH OTHER'S
THROATS SINCE HE SPIKED MY KNEE AND RUINED MY CAREER.

00:17:02.021 --> 00:17:06.108
ACCIDENTS HAPPEN,
GEORGE. IT WASN'T AN ACCIDENT.

00:17:06.692 --> 00:17:09.611
WHEN YOU SLIDE INTO A CATCHER
WITH YOUR NAILS UP, IT'S ON PURPOSE.

00:17:10.195 --> 00:17:12.530
I WAS COMIN' INTO
MY BEST YEARS.

00:17:12.531 --> 00:17:15.450
NOW, DON'T GO MAKIN'
MORE COW-PIES TO STEP IN, GEORGE.

00:17:15.451 --> 00:17:18.954
<i>YOU GOT ENOUGH MANURE</i>
<i>ON YOUR BOOTS NOW.</i>

00:17:18.954 --> 00:17:21.289
CONTROL YOURSELF TODAY.

00:17:21.290 --> 00:17:23.375
[ Chattering ]

00:17:26.295 --> 00:17:30.382
[ Announcer ]  LADIES AND
GENTLEMEN, A REMINDER THAT EVERY WEDNESDAY IS KID'S DAY.

00:17:30.382 --> 00:17:33.885
WHOA!  I SEE BETTER SEATS!
MUCH BETTER SEATS! COME ON, J.P.

00:17:34.470 --> 00:17:37.973
...ANY RESERVED SEATS AND $1.00
DISCOUNTS ON GENERAL ADMISSION. COME ON!

00:17:38.557 --> 00:17:41.476
TICKETS ARE AVAILABLE THE DAY OF
THE GAME AT THE ANAHEIM STADIUM BOX OFFICE. ALL RIGHT!

00:17:41.477 --> 00:17:44.396
THANK YOU.
GREAT SEATS. YEAH.

00:17:44.396 --> 00:17:47.899
THIS IS MUCH BETTER
THAN THE TREE. I'LL SAY.

00:17:53.155 --> 00:17:57.826
HEY, SKIP.  TRAINER SAYS
I'M READY TO PITCH.  WHEN AM I GETTIN' OFF THE INJURED LIST?

00:17:58.410 --> 00:18:03.081
HOW'S NEVER SOUND?  YOU'RE HERE
'CAUSE YOU GOT A CONTRACT THAT PAYS YOU TO BE HERE.

00:18:03.082 --> 00:18:06.585
YOU BLEW YOUR ARM OUT.
PLAYED ON TOO MANY PAIN PILLS.

00:18:06.585 --> 00:18:10.672
PAIN PILLS?  YOU WERE THE ONE
STUFFIN' 'EM DOWN MY THROAT FIVE YEARS AGO IN CINCINNATI.

00:18:10.672 --> 00:18:14.175
HEY, IT WAS YOUR DECISION
TO SWALLOW 'EM.  I HAD A BRAIN.

00:18:14.760 --> 00:18:18.263
WHEN YOU WERE FINISHED,
I TRADED YOU.  I NEVER THOUGHT I'D GET STUCK WITH YOU AGAIN.

00:18:18.263 --> 00:18:21.182
WHY, YOU ROTTEN--
[ Coughing ]

00:18:21.183 --> 00:18:24.686
THAT'S NOT CONTAGIOUS,
IS IT?  OUTTA MY WAY. I GOT A BALL CLUB TO MANAGE.

00:18:24.686 --> 00:18:27.021
[ Crowd ]
♪ AND THE ROCKET'S RED GLARE ♪

00:18:27.022 --> 00:18:32.277
♪ THE BOMBS BURSTING
IN AIR ♪

00:18:32.277 --> 00:18:35.780
♪ GAVE PROOF
THROUGH THE NIGHT ♪

00:18:35.781 --> 00:18:39.284
♪ THAT OUR FLAG
WAS STILL THERE ♪

00:18:39.284 --> 00:18:43.955
♪ OH, SAY DOES THAT
STAR-SPANGLED ♪

00:18:43.956 --> 00:18:48.043
♪ BANNER YET WAVE ♪

00:18:48.043 --> 00:18:52.714
♪ O'ER THE LAND
OF THE FREE ♪

00:18:52.714 --> 00:18:59.137
♪ AND THE HOME
OF THE BRAVE ♪

00:18:59.138 --> 00:19:00.889
WHOO-OO!
[ Crowd Cheering ]

00:19:03.225 --> 00:19:06.144
I GUESS NO MATTER HOW MANY TIMES
YOU HEAR THAT SONG PLAYED...

00:19:06.145 --> 00:19:09.064
IN A MAJOR-LEAGUE STADIUM
ON A WARM AFTERNOON,

00:19:09.064 --> 00:19:11.983
IT'S STILL
EMOTIONALLY EVOCATIVE.

00:19:11.984 --> 00:19:16.655
DROP DEAD.
I GOT SUNSCREEN IN MY EYES.

00:19:16.655 --> 00:19:20.158
WILL I WIN, WILL I WIN,
WILL I WIN, WIN, WIN?

00:19:20.159 --> 00:19:21.910
AW!

00:19:23.662 --> 00:19:27.165
YEAH!
♪ JOSE, CAN YOU SEE ♪

00:19:27.166 --> 00:19:31.253
WAIT A SECOND.  THE FIST WORD
IS JOSE?  I THOUGHT IT WAS-- IT'S JOSE.  WE KNOW.

00:19:31.253 --> 00:19:36.508
WOW!  IT'S ABOUT
A SPANISH GUY! ♪ JO-JOSE, CAN YOU SEE ♪

00:19:36.508 --> 00:19:38.259
I DON'T BELIEVE HIM.
IT'S SO EASY.

00:19:40.012 --> 00:19:42.931
[ Wilder ]
WHIT BASS TAKES THE MOUND WITH HIS TRADEMARK SLIDE.

00:19:42.931 --> 00:19:47.018
HIS ODDBALL ANTICS ARE BY NOW
WELL KNOWN TO THE FANS.

00:19:47.019 --> 00:19:49.354
[ Color Man ]  THAT'S RIGHT,
RANCH.  THIS SEASON ALONE WE'VE SEEN HIM LICK DIRT,

00:19:49.938 --> 00:19:54.609
EAT BUGS AND FLOSS HIS
CATCHER'S TEETH IN THE DUGOUT.

00:19:54.610 --> 00:19:58.113
NONE OF THAT, MAY I ADD,
SEEMS TO HAVE HELPED HIS PITCHING.

00:19:58.113 --> 00:20:01.032
HE'S TWO AND ELEVEN.

00:20:01.033 --> 00:20:04.536
[ Grunts ]
[ Announcer ]  LEADING OFF FOR THE BLUE JAYS, NUMBER 22,

00:20:05.120 --> 00:20:08.623
THIRD BASEMAN,
OWEN FARLEY.

00:20:08.624 --> 00:20:12.711
[ Wilder ]
AND AFTER HARDLY ANY WARM-UP, BASS SIGNALS HE'S READY.

00:20:12.711 --> 00:20:15.046
[ Crowd Muttering ]

00:20:16.798 --> 00:20:20.301
[ Sniffing ]
MM!  HMM, HMM!

00:20:20.302 --> 00:20:22.637
[ Yawning ]

00:20:22.638 --> 00:20:24.389
[ Grunts ]
HUH? [ Bat Cracking ]

00:20:24.389 --> 00:20:26.724
[ Grunts ]

00:20:26.725 --> 00:20:32.564
[ Wilder ]  FIRST PITCH
OF THE GAME AND THE ANGELS HAVE AN ERROR AND A MAN ON BASE.

00:20:32.564 --> 00:20:36.067
SO THE FIFTH INNING
GOES INTO THE BOOKS WITH THE SCORE NOTHING TO NOTHING.

00:20:36.068 --> 00:20:39.571
THE ANGELS THUS FAR
HAVE BEEN ABLE TO KEEP THE HARD-HITTING BLUE JAYS SILENT.

00:20:39.571 --> 00:20:43.074
BUT AS WE HEAD INTO THE SIXTH,
THE JAYS HAVE THE MIDDLE OF THE ORDER COMING UP...

00:20:43.075 --> 00:20:46.578
WITH THE EVER-DANGEROUS
ASHER LAZZATO LEADING OFF.

00:20:46.578 --> 00:20:51.249
[ Announcer ]
NUMBER 31, LEFT FIELDER, ASHER LAZZATO.

00:20:53.585 --> 00:20:58.256
[ Wilder ]  BASS SETS...
AND SETS... AND SETS AGAIN.

00:20:58.257 --> 00:21:00.592
PLEASE,
JUST THROW THE BALL.

00:21:02.344 --> 00:21:04.679
HERE'S THE PITCH.

00:21:04.680 --> 00:21:08.183
AND LAZZATO SMASHES ONE
TO DEEP CENTER!

00:21:08.183 --> 00:21:11.102
- <i>I DON'T THINK WILLIAMS'LL</i>
<i>GET TO THIS ONE.</i> <i>- [ Panting ]</i>

00:21:33.292 --> 00:21:35.043
OH!

00:21:35.043 --> 00:21:37.378
[ Screaming ]

00:21:37.379 --> 00:21:40.298
[ Wilder ]
AND BEN WILLIAMS MAKES A MIRACULOUS CATCH.

00:21:40.882 --> 00:21:44.385
- HOLY COW!
- HOW'D HE DO THAT?

00:21:44.386 --> 00:21:46.137
YEAH, HOLY COW!

00:21:46.138 --> 00:21:48.473
HOW'D HE DO THAT?
HOW DID HE DO THAT?

00:21:51.977 --> 00:21:55.480
THAT, SPORTS FANS, IS A PLAY
YOU'RE GOING TO SEE RUN...

00:21:55.480 --> 00:21:59.567
IN BASEBALL HIGHLIGHTS
FOR YEARS TO COME.

00:21:59.568 --> 00:22:02.487
GET ME SOMETHING HERE!
COME ON, COME ON! WE GOT IT.

00:22:02.487 --> 00:22:06.574
GET ME SOMETHING!
I'M HANGIN', I'M HANGIN'! THIS IS DEAD AIRTIME!

00:22:06.575 --> 00:22:10.662
DID YOU SEE THAT?
YEAH, AWESOME.

00:22:10.662 --> 00:22:14.165
THEY WERE JUST SUCKED DOWN
RIGHT FROM THE SKY. WHO?

00:22:14.750 --> 00:22:17.669
<i>THOSE GUYS.  THOSE GUYS</i>
<i>IN SPARKLING PAJAMAS.</i>

00:22:17.669 --> 00:22:23.508
WHAT ARE YOU TALKING ABOUT,
ROGER?  WHAT GUYS IN SPARKLING PAJAMAS?

00:22:23.508 --> 00:22:26.427
YOU DIDN'T SEE 'EM?
THOSE GUYS CARRYING WILLIAMS?

00:22:26.428 --> 00:22:31.099
-I DON'T KNOW.
-HEY, MISTER, DID YOU SEE THAT?

00:22:31.099 --> 00:22:34.602
LUCKY CATCH.
NO, DID YOU SEE WHAT HAPPENED WITH THE CLOUDS?

00:22:34.603 --> 00:22:36.938
DID YOU SEE
THE PEOPLE WITH WILLIAMS WHEN HE CAUGHT THE BALL?

00:22:36.938 --> 00:22:39.273
HUH?

00:22:39.274 --> 00:22:42.777
THERE WERE SHINY PEOPLE OUT
THERE.  FLYING, SHINY PEOPLE.

00:22:42.778 --> 00:22:46.865
[ Slurping ]
YEAH, WELL, TELL YOUR PARENTS ABOUT IT.

00:22:46.865 --> 00:22:52.704
BUT THE--
[ Announcer ]  NUMBER 58, THE IRVINATOR, IRVING NATOR.

00:22:52.704 --> 00:22:54.455
[ Belching ]

00:22:57.959 --> 00:23:00.294
YOU DIDN'T SEE 'EM?

00:23:00.295 --> 00:23:03.798
IT WAS A REAL GOOD PLAY, ROGER.
I SAW THAT.

00:23:03.799 --> 00:23:06.134
YES!  YES!

00:23:06.134 --> 00:23:10.805
AMAZING PLAY.
I LOVE IT WHEN THEY COME FROM ABOVE LIKE THAT.

00:23:10.806 --> 00:23:13.725
FROM-FROM ABOVE?

00:23:13.725 --> 00:23:16.644
THE SKY DEAL.
IT'S A GOOD ENTRANCE FOR 'EM.

00:23:16.645 --> 00:23:18.980
YOU MEAN YOU SAW 'EM?
THE ANGELS?

00:23:20.148 --> 00:23:24.819
- ANGELS?
- <i>COURSE I SAW 'EM.</i> <i>THEY'RE WITH ME.</i>

00:23:24.820 --> 00:23:27.739
THE LITTLE ONE'S A ROOKIE.
JUST GOT OFF HIS TRAINING WINGS.

00:23:27.739 --> 00:23:31.826
YOU MEAN THO-THOSE ARE...
REAL... ANGELS?

00:23:31.827 --> 00:23:34.162
ACCEPT NO SUBSTITUTES.

00:23:34.162 --> 00:23:37.081
WHO ARE YOU?

00:23:37.082 --> 00:23:41.753
JUST CALL ME AL.
NO ONE CAN SEE ME OR HEAR ME BUT YOU.

00:23:41.753 --> 00:23:43.504
W-WHY ME?

00:23:43.505 --> 00:23:45.840
YOU ASKED FOR HELP
AND WE'RE HERE.

00:23:45.841 --> 00:23:48.760
WE COME AND GO.
IT'S AN "AS NEEDED" SITUATION.

00:23:48.760 --> 00:23:52.263
WHO YOU
TALKIN' TO, ROG?

00:23:52.264 --> 00:23:55.183
WHAT ARE YOU
TALKIN' ABOUT? TUBBY'S BACK.

00:23:55.183 --> 00:24:01.022
I'M VAPOR.
KEEP YOUR NOSE CLEAN AND YOUR HEART OPEN.

00:24:01.022 --> 00:24:04.525
BUT ANGELS ARE AROUND, SONNY.
WE'LL BE IN TOUCH.

00:24:05.110 --> 00:24:06.861
[ Grunting ]

00:24:06.862 --> 00:24:09.781
AL!  WHAT--

00:24:09.781 --> 00:24:11.532
[ Belching ]

00:24:15.620 --> 00:24:19.707
WHO'S AL?
HE'S THE--

00:24:20.876 --> 00:24:23.211
<i>WHAT'S YOUR PROBLEM?</i>

00:24:25.547 --> 00:24:27.882
ARE YOU SICK
OR SOMETHIN'?

00:24:27.883 --> 00:24:30.802
YEAH, MAYBE.

00:24:30.802 --> 00:24:32.553
GET YOUR PIZZA,
HOT PIZZA.

00:24:32.554 --> 00:24:35.473
[ Wilder ]
WITH TWO OUTS, THIS IS THE ANGELS' LAST CHANCE...

00:24:35.474 --> 00:24:37.809
TO PUT AWAY THE JAYS
BEFORE EXTRA INNINGS.

00:24:37.809 --> 00:24:41.312
NEXT UP IS MESSMER
WHO, UNFORTUNATELY, HAS BEEN HITLESS...

00:24:41.313 --> 00:24:44.232
IN HIS LAST 26 AT BATS.

00:24:44.232 --> 00:24:47.735
[ Announcer ]  NUMBER 14,
CATCHER TRISCUIT MESSMER. TIME.

00:24:57.078 --> 00:24:59.413
Nh
HERE WE GO AGAIN.

00:25:21.019 --> 00:25:24.522
[ Wilder ]
AND THAT ONE, LADIES AND GENTS, IS HEADIN' DOWNTOWN...

00:25:24.523 --> 00:25:28.026
AND MESSMER BREAKS A BAT AND
THE ANGELS' LOSING STREAK... [ Cheering ]

00:25:28.026 --> 00:25:31.529
AS HE CRASHES A HOME RUN
IN THE NINTH TO WIN THE GAME.

00:25:31.530 --> 00:25:33.281
[ Chuckling ]

00:25:37.369 --> 00:25:39.704
[ Grunts ]

00:25:40.872 --> 00:25:43.207
<i>[ Players Hooting,</i>
<i>Cheering ]</i>

00:25:45.544 --> 00:25:47.879
OH, YEAH!

00:25:49.631 --> 00:25:51.966
WE WON?

00:25:54.302 --> 00:25:57.805
YEAH, YEAH, YEAH
YEAH, YEAH, YEAH!

00:25:57.806 --> 00:26:01.309
HOW DID THAT HAPPEN?

00:26:01.309 --> 00:26:04.812
YEAH, HA!

00:26:04.813 --> 00:26:08.316
BUT... YOU DIDN'T SEE
THE ANGEL WITH HIM? WE WON.

00:26:08.316 --> 00:26:12.987
BUT THERE WERE
ANGELS IN THE OUTFIELD AND IN THE INFIELD.

00:26:12.988 --> 00:26:15.907
YEAH, NINE OF 'EM.
[ Groaning ]

00:26:15.907 --> 00:26:19.410
[ Announcer ]
LADIES AND GENTLEMEN, OUR FINAL DRAWING THIS AFTERNOON...

00:26:19.411 --> 00:26:22.330
WILL GIVE THREE LUCKY WINNERS
A CHANCE TO BE PHOTOGRAPHED ON THE FIELD...

00:26:22.330 --> 00:26:26.417
WITH MANAGER GEORGE KNOX.
THAT'S A PRIZE? MM-MM.

00:26:26.418 --> 00:26:31.673
THE FIRST WINNING TICKET
IS NUMBER 4-7-7-3-8-0.

00:26:31.673 --> 00:26:34.008
I WON.
WHAT?

00:26:35.760 --> 00:26:39.263
YOU DO IT.  I DON'T WANNA
HAVE MY PICTURE TAKEN.

00:26:39.264 --> 00:26:42.767
I DON'T LIKE STRANGERS.

00:26:42.767 --> 00:26:46.270
GEEZ.  WHAT'S GOIN' ON
AROUND HERE?

00:26:46.271 --> 00:26:48.606
[ Announcer ]  THE SERIES
AGAINST THE OAKLAND A's... [ Chuckling ]

00:26:48.607 --> 00:26:52.694
OPENING FRIDAY
HERE AT THE ANAHEIM STADIUM. WHO'S HE?

00:26:52.694 --> 00:26:56.781
<i>I CAN SEE YOU KIDS</i>
<i>DON'T KNOW YOUR BASEBALL.</i> <i>THAT'S MEL CLARK.</i>

00:26:56.781 --> 00:27:02.620
MEL CLARK?  WHOA, HE PITCHED
THREE SHUTOUTS IN A ROW FOR CINCINNATI IN 1986.

00:27:02.621 --> 00:27:05.540
<i>WELL, THAT'S RIGHT.</i>
<i>MY DAD USED TO</i> <i>TALK ABOUT HIM.</i>

00:27:05.540 --> 00:27:09.043
YOU USED TO BE
MEL CLARK?

00:27:09.044 --> 00:27:11.963
YEAH, I USED TO BE.

00:27:11.963 --> 00:27:15.466
- COME ON, SON.  LET'S GO.
- THAT'S IT.  THAT'S ALL, FOLKS.

00:27:15.467 --> 00:27:17.802
OKAY, WE HAVE THREE PHOTO OPS.
IT'LL BE QUICK.

00:27:17.802 --> 00:27:19.553
GIVE 'EM PUBLICITY STILLS.
IT'LL BE QUICKER.

00:27:19.554 --> 00:27:22.473
THEY WANT A PICTURE WITH YOU.
THEY'RE ALL KIDS. I HATE KIDS.

00:27:22.474 --> 00:27:25.393
YEAH, I GUESSED THAT.

00:27:27.729 --> 00:27:30.648
[ Whistles ]
FIRST KID!

00:27:31.816 --> 00:27:34.735
J.P., WAIT!
WELL--  HE--

00:27:46.998 --> 00:27:49.917
LOOKS LIKE
A PRISON PHOTO.

00:27:49.918 --> 00:27:54.005
UH, WOULD EITHER OF YOU
MIND SMILING? THE TEAM DID JUST WIN.

00:27:54.005 --> 00:27:57.508
IT WAS A MISTAKE.
THIS TEAM CAN'T WIN.

00:27:57.509 --> 00:28:01.596
THEY WON 'CAUSE THERE
WERE ANGELS OUT THERE. HUH?

00:28:01.596 --> 00:28:03.931
REAL ONES.
I SAW 'EM.

00:28:03.932 --> 00:28:06.851
TWO ANGELS CAME OUT OF THE SKY
AND THEY PICKED UP BEN WILLIAMS.

00:28:06.851 --> 00:28:10.938
AND ANOTHER ANGEL
HIT MESSMER'S HOME RUN. THAT'S WHY THE BAT BROKE.

00:28:10.939 --> 00:28:15.610
GREAT, A PSYCHO KID.
DAVID, YOU THINK THEY'D SCREEN THESE PEOPLE.

00:28:17.362 --> 00:28:22.033
IT'S TRUE!  ASK WILLIAMS
ABOUT IT.  OR MESSMER.

00:28:22.033 --> 00:28:24.952
THEY'LL TELL YOU
SOMETHIN'S GOIN' ON. YOU'LL SEE.

00:28:33.545 --> 00:28:35.880
[ Sewing Machine
Clicking, Whirring ]

00:28:50.478 --> 00:28:53.981
HONEY, WHY AREN'T
YOU ASLEEP? I GOTTA ASK YOU SOMETHIN'.DH

00:28:53.982 --> 00:28:56.901
DO YOU BELIEVE
IN ANGELS?

00:28:56.901 --> 00:29:01.572
WHAT DO ANGELS GOTTA DO WITH
YOU BEIN' OUT OF YOUR BED?

00:29:01.573 --> 00:29:05.076
NO, I REALLY WANNA KNOW.
DO YOU THINK THEY'RE REAL?

00:29:07.412 --> 00:29:12.667
WELL, THERE ARE A LOT
OF AMAZING THINGS IN LIFE THAT JUST CAN'T BE EXPLAINED.

00:29:12.667 --> 00:29:14.418
UH--

00:29:14.419 --> 00:29:16.754
I BELIEVE IN, UH...

00:29:16.755 --> 00:29:20.258
THE POSSIBILITY
OF MIRACULOUS THINGS HAPPENING.

00:29:20.258 --> 00:29:23.177
THAT'S WHAT MAKES EVERY DAY OF
OUR LIVES WORTH GETTING UP FOR.

00:29:23.178 --> 00:29:26.681
SO, UMM--

00:29:26.681 --> 00:29:30.768
YEAH.  I GUESS I DO
BELIEVE IN ANGELS.

00:29:30.769 --> 00:29:32.520
YEAH.

00:29:34.272 --> 00:29:37.191
ME TOO.
GOOD NIGHT, MAGGIE.

00:29:37.192 --> 00:29:38.943
NIGHT.

00:29:43.031 --> 00:29:45.950
HUH!
[ Whirring, Clicking Resumes ]

00:30:01.132 --> 00:30:02.883
NICE CATCH
YESTERDAY, BEN.

00:30:02.884 --> 00:30:07.555
HOW DID IT FEEL?
OR DID IT ALL HAPPEN SO FAST YOU DON'T EVEN REMEMBER?

00:30:07.555 --> 00:30:11.058
[ Williams ]
