LADIES AND GENTLEMEN,
CAN WE NOW SAY THE ANGELS ARE ON A WINNING STREAK?

00:44:37.424 --> 00:44:43.263
OR WERE THESE LAST FEW GAMES
JUST A SMALL BLIP ON THE SCREEN OF A TERMINALLY ILL PATIENT?

00:44:43.263 --> 00:44:45.598
[ Chuckles ]
ONLY TIME WILL TELL.

00:44:45.599 --> 00:44:49.686
WHAT IS GOING ON?
WHERE ARE MY STATS? I'M ON THE AIR!

00:44:49.687 --> 00:44:53.774
MY ASS IS HANGING ON THE AIR,
AND THERE ARE NO STATS. HOW MANY ERRORS?

00:44:54.358 --> 00:44:57.277
THERE WERE A LOT OF ERRORS.
NOT AS MANY AS IN THIS BOOTH.

00:44:57.277 --> 00:45:01.364
LET ME TELL YOU,
THIS <i>IS NOT BASEBALL.é4</i>

00:45:01.365 --> 00:45:03.533
OW!
DAVID.

00:45:03.534 --> 00:45:08.789
WHATEVER YOUR DUTIES BEFORE,
FORGET 'EM.  FROM NOW ON, THESE BOYS WILL BE AT ALL OUR GAMES.

00:45:08.789 --> 00:45:11.124
[ Together ]
ALL RIGHT! THAT'S YOUR JOB.

00:45:11.125 --> 00:45:14.628
I WANT TO REMIND YOU,
YOU ARE GONNA FIRE ME ON FRIDAY, AREN'T YOU?

00:45:15.212 --> 00:45:16.963
YOU'VE BONDED
WITH THE BOYS. BONDED?

00:45:16.964 --> 00:45:19.883
YOU'RE GONNA STICK AROUND,
DAVID. YEAH, STICK AROUND.

00:45:19.883 --> 00:45:23.970
YOU GOT JOB SECURITY.
JOB SECURITY? WHO KNEW?

00:45:23.971 --> 00:45:26.890
SO, YOU'RE RIGHT.
HEMMERLING CAME THROUGH.

00:45:26.890 --> 00:45:29.809
- YEAH, 'CAUSE THE ANGEL.
- AH, WHATEVER.

00:45:29.810 --> 00:45:34.481
-WE GOT ANGELS HELPING THE TEAM.
-AH, WELL, THAT MAY BE, BUT WE'RE WINNING.

00:45:34.481 --> 00:45:37.984
YEAH.  ALL THE GAMES, MAN!
CAN YOU BELIEVE IT?

00:45:37.985 --> 00:45:41.488
<i>WHEN WE'RE ON THE ROAD,</i>
<i>YOU SHOULD WATCH THE GAMES</i> <i>ON TV.</i>

00:45:41.488 --> 00:45:43.823
WE'LL FIGURE OUT A WAY
FOR US TO TALK ON THE PHONE.

00:45:43.824 --> 00:45:46.743
YOU MEAN, THE PHONE
IN THE DUGOUT YOU'RE ALWAYS YELLIN' INTO...

00:45:46.744 --> 00:45:49.663
AND BANGING AGAINST THE WALL
AND SPITTING AT? YEAH.

00:45:49.663 --> 00:45:51.998
YEAH.
COOL!

00:45:53.751 --> 00:45:57.838
<i>WHAT A GAME.  FIRST TIME</i>
<i>HEMMERLING GOT A HIT,</i> <i>LET ALONE A HOME RUN.</i>

00:45:57.838 --> 00:46:02.509
IT 'CAUSE OF THE ANGELS;
THEY HELPED HIM. GET IN.

00:46:02.509 --> 00:46:05.428
COME ON.
WE DON'T HAVE ALL DAY.

00:46:05.429 --> 00:46:08.932
J.P. DOESN'T RIDE IN CARS.
WHAT'S THE PROBLEM? HE GETS CARSICK?

00:46:08.932 --> 00:46:12.435
SORT OF.
HE USED TO LIVE IN A CAR WITH HIS MOM.

00:46:12.436 --> 00:46:17.691
HE SLEPT IN THE FRONT CURLED UP
LIKE A CAT.  WHEN HE GETS IN, HIS STOMACHACHE COMES BACK.

00:46:21.195 --> 00:46:23.530
[ Horn Honking Loudly ]

00:46:38.712 --> 00:46:41.047
<i>I'LL CALL YOU TOMORROW.</i>
<i>ALL RIGHT.</i>

00:46:41.048 --> 00:46:43.383
THANK YOU
FOR THE RIDE HOME.

00:46:43.383 --> 00:46:45.718
HE SPEAKS?

00:46:47.471 --> 00:46:50.390
HI.
YOU GUYS HAVE A GOOD TIME? HI.

00:46:50.974 --> 00:46:52.725
A BLAST!
WE WON!

00:46:52.726 --> 00:46:55.645
GREAT.
WHERE'S MIGUEL?

00:46:55.646 --> 00:47:00.317
I BOUGHT HIM ALL SORTS OF STUFF.
MIGUEL GOT PLACED IN A FOSTER HOME THIS AFTERNOON.

00:47:00.901 --> 00:47:03.820
HE GOT PLACED?
MIGUEL'S GONE?

00:47:04.404 --> 00:47:05.571
MM-HMM.

00:47:05.572 --> 00:47:08.491
WHERE?
WITH WHO?

00:47:08.492 --> 00:47:10.827
A REAL NICE FAMILY
FROM NORTHRIDGE.

00:47:10.828 --> 00:47:14.331
[ Crying ]
I'M GONNA MISS HIM. I REALLY LIKED MIGUEL.

00:47:17.251 --> 00:47:20.170
I ONLY HAVE A LICENSE
FOR SHORT-TERM CARE.

00:47:20.170 --> 00:47:23.089
YOU KNOW, MIGUEL'S BEEN
HERE FOR SIX MONTHS. SEVEN.

00:47:23.090 --> 00:47:25.425
SEVEN MONTHS!
RIGHT.

00:47:25.425 --> 00:47:29.512
THAT'S WHAT HAPPENS,
YOU KNOW?  I MEAN... YOU UNDERSTAND THAT, ROGER?

00:47:29.513 --> 00:47:33.016
OH, DON'T FEEL BAD, MAGGIE.

00:47:33.016 --> 00:47:37.103
I BET WE'LL SEE HIM AGAIN.
MAYBE IN COURT OR SOMETHING.

00:47:37.688 --> 00:47:40.023
OH, ROGER.
[ Sighs ]

00:47:40.607 --> 00:47:42.942
GOD FORBID.

00:47:45.279 --> 00:47:47.614
ROGER?

00:47:47.614 --> 00:47:51.701
WHAT?
ARE YOU ASLEEP?

00:47:52.286 --> 00:47:55.205
IF I WAS ASLEEP,
HOW WOULD I BE TALKIN' TO YOU?

00:47:55.789 --> 00:47:58.124
YOU COULD BE "SLEEPTALKING."

00:48:00.460 --> 00:48:04.547
[ Sighs ]
LOOK, I'LL GIVE A DIME TOMORROW IF YOU DON'T SAY ANOTHER WORD.

00:48:05.716 --> 00:48:08.051
OKAY.

00:48:11.555 --> 00:48:13.890
<i>ROGER?</i>
<i>[ Groans ]</i>

00:48:13.891 --> 00:48:16.810
YOU CAN FORGET
THAT DIME.

00:48:18.562 --> 00:48:22.065
DO YOU THINK YOUR PARENTS
ARE GONNA EVER COME GET YOU?

00:48:22.065 --> 00:48:24.400
I DON'T KNOW.

00:48:24.401 --> 00:48:28.488
MOM'S NOT ALIVE,
BUT... MY DAD'S GONNA COME GET ME.

00:48:28.488 --> 00:48:30.823
<i>I'M SURE OF IT.</i>

00:48:30.824 --> 00:48:33.743
YOU THINK MY MOM'S
GONNA EVER COME GET ME?

00:48:34.912 --> 00:48:37.247
MAYBE,
YOU KNOW.

00:48:37.247 --> 00:48:39.582
IT COULD HAPPEN.

00:48:40.751 --> 00:48:44.254
YEAH...
IT COULD HAPPEN.

00:48:48.342 --> 00:48:50.677
ROGER?
WHAT?

00:48:50.677 --> 00:48:53.596
I'M HAPPY
YOU SEE THE ANGELS.

00:48:57.100 --> 00:48:58.851
ME TOO.

00:49:01.188 --> 00:49:03.523
GOOD NIGHT.

00:49:07.611 --> 00:49:10.530
[ Wilder ]
IT'S A BEAUTIFUL DAY HERE IN ANAHEIM...

00:49:11.114 --> 00:49:15.785
AS THE RESURGENT ANGELS
PREPARE TO MEET THEIR LONGTIME NEMESIS, THE DETROIT TIGERS...

00:49:16.370 --> 00:49:19.289
WHO HAVE WON
THE FIRST FIVE GAMES OF THEIR WESTERN ROAD TRIP.

00:49:19.289 --> 00:49:23.960
[ Wally ]  THEY'VE BEEN
THE HOTTEST TEAM IN THE LEAGUE FOR THE LAST FEW WEEKS, RANCH.

00:49:25.712 --> 00:49:28.631
[ Announcer ]
COMING UP NEXT WEEK, "CAP NIGHT."

00:49:28.632 --> 00:49:33.887
THIS WILL FEATURE A TOTALLY
WHITE CAP WITH RED PINSTRIPES AND THE ANGELS LOGO.

00:49:33.887 --> 00:49:38.558
IT'S FREE
FOR THE FIRST 50,000 FANS ENTERING ANAHEIM STADIUM.

00:49:47.317 --> 00:49:50.236
- I SEE AN ANGEL.
- ALREADY?

00:49:51.989 --> 00:49:56.076
I GOTTA GO BATHROOM.
I CAN'T GO ALONE. BAD GUYS MIGHT GET ME.

00:49:56.660 --> 00:49:58.995
YOU JUST CAME BACK
FROM THE BATHROOM.

00:49:58.996 --> 00:50:01.915
I'VE GOTTA GO NOW.
SORRY. GIMME YOUR COKE.

00:50:03.083 --> 00:50:06.002
GIMME THE CRACKER JACKS.
STAND UP.

00:50:06.003 --> 00:50:07.754
GO.

00:50:15.929 --> 00:50:18.848
WHAT'S UP?
WE GOT AN ANGEL.

00:50:20.017 --> 00:50:22.352
BUT THE GAME
HASN'T STARTED.

00:50:23.520 --> 00:50:25.855
SHE WAS WITH MEL CLARK.

00:50:35.782 --> 00:50:37.533
AH, IMPOSSIBLE.

00:50:37.534 --> 00:50:40.453
SHE WAS THERE.
THAT MEANS MEL SHOULD START THE GAME TODAY.

00:50:40.454 --> 00:50:43.373
MEL'S ARM IS GONE.
I DON'T CARE. HE SHOULD START THE GAME.

00:50:43.373 --> 00:50:46.292
NO WAY!
BESIDES, HE'S NOT EVEN ON THE ACTIVE ROSTER.

00:50:46.293 --> 00:50:49.796
IF THE ANGEL PITCHES
WITH HIM, HE'LL BE AWESOME.

00:51:02.059 --> 00:51:04.978
YOU REALLY DO SEE SOMETHING,
DON'T YOU?

00:51:06.730 --> 00:51:09.065
YEAH...
I DO.

00:51:26.583 --> 00:51:28.918
GOOD.
ALL RIGHT.

00:51:42.349 --> 00:51:44.684
[ Sighs ]

00:51:46.436 --> 00:51:49.939
YOU'RE OFF INJURED RESERVE
AND YOU'RE STARTING TODAY.

00:51:49.940 --> 00:51:52.275
YOU TALKIN' TO ME?

00:51:52.275 --> 00:51:56.946
YEAH.  SO GET
YOUR STUFF TOGETHER.

00:52:02.202 --> 00:52:05.705
[ Wilder ]
THE STARTING PITCHER ANNOUNCED FOR THIS GAME WAS DAN PRINCE.

00:52:05.705 --> 00:52:08.624
BUT JUST MOMENTS AGO, THE ANGELS
MADE A DRAMATIC CHANGE...

00:52:09.209 --> 00:52:11.544
AND ACTIVATED
THE LONG-INJURED MEL CLARK.

00:52:11.545 --> 00:52:15.632
LEAGUE RULES SPECIFY THAT UP
UNTIL THE FIRST PITCH IS THROWN, THE ROSTER CAN BE ALTERED,

00:52:15.632 --> 00:52:19.719
ALTHOUGH I CAN'T EVER
REMEMBER THIS HAPPENING SO NEAR GAME TIME.

00:52:19.719 --> 00:52:21.470
[ Flips Switch On ]
ME EITHER, RANCH.

00:52:22.055 --> 00:52:24.974
EASY, WALLY.
LESS IS MORE.

00:52:26.143 --> 00:52:29.646
THESE WARM-UPS
SHOULD BE INTERESTING. [ Grunts ]

00:52:29.646 --> 00:52:31.981
OVER THE PLATE, MAN!

00:52:31.982 --> 00:52:36.069
<i>[ Wally ]</i>
<i>CLARK LOOKS A LITTLE RUSTY.</i>

00:52:36.069 --> 00:52:38.404
TOO MUCH TIME
IN THE WHIRLPOOL, WALLY.

00:52:38.405 --> 00:52:41.324
[ Spits ]
I'M CHECKING TO SEE...

00:52:41.908 --> 00:52:44.827
IF DAN PRINCE PULLED
A MUSCLE DURING HIS WARM-UP.

00:52:44.828 --> 00:52:50.083
THERE MUST BE SOME LOGICAL
EXPLANATION AS TO WHY KNOX WOULD MAKE SUCH A BIZARRE CHANGE.

00:52:50.667 --> 00:52:53.586
I HAVE PERSONALLY CHECKED
THE STATS, SPORTS FANS,

00:52:53.587 --> 00:52:58.842
AND MEL CLARK HASN'T STARTED
A GAME... IN THIS DECADE.

00:52:58.842 --> 00:53:03.513
<i>[ Wally ]</i>
<i>HE LOOKS MIGHTY NERVOUS</i> <i>OUT THERE.</i>

00:53:03.513 --> 00:53:05.848
NOT AS NERVOUS
AS GEORGE KNOX.

00:53:24.534 --> 00:53:26.869
CLARK TAKES THE SIGN.

00:53:30.957 --> 00:53:33.292
TALK ABOUT HEAT!
MESSMER FELT THAT ONE. OW!

00:53:33.293 --> 00:53:36.796
- [ Crowd Cheering ]
- WOW!

00:53:36.796 --> 00:53:40.883
WHAT AN AMAZING PITCH!
YOU DAMN-- DARN RIGHT.

00:53:43.220 --> 00:53:45.555
[ Wilder ]
WELL, COMMIT THAT TO MEMORY, WALLY,

00:53:45.555 --> 00:53:49.058
'CAUSE HE DOESN'T HAVE
ANY MORE OF THOSE IN HIM.

00:53:49.059 --> 00:53:51.978
AN ANGEL HELPED OUT
ON THAT ONE. GOOD.

00:53:53.146 --> 00:53:56.065
STRIKE!
[ Crowd Cheers ]

00:53:56.066 --> 00:53:58.401
- <i>[ Ball Pops Into Glove ]</i>
<i>- STRIKE!</i>

00:53:58.401 --> 00:54:00.736
MEL!

00:54:00.737 --> 00:54:03.072
WAY TO GO!
ALL RIGHT, MEL!

00:54:03.073 --> 00:54:07.160
[ Grunting ]

00:54:10.080 --> 00:54:14.167
IT'S NOW THE TOP OF THE NINTH.
THERE ARE TWO OUTS. WE'VE GOT A FULL COUNT.

00:54:14.167 --> 00:54:17.670
- THIS COULD BE THE TIGERS' LAST
CHANCE TO GET BACK IN THIS GAME. - ONE MORE.

00:54:17.671 --> 00:54:20.590
<i>[ Crowd Cheering ]</i>

00:54:20.590 --> 00:54:22.341
[ Grunts ]

00:54:29.349 --> 00:54:31.100
I TOLD YOU!
I TOLD YOU!

00:54:33.436 --> 00:54:38.691
[ Wilder ]  THAT'S THE GAME!
THE ANGELS WIN 1-NOTHING IN A MIRACLE SHUTOUT...

00:54:38.692 --> 00:54:41.027
PITCHED BY THE VETERAN,
MEL CLARK.

00:54:43.363 --> 00:54:46.866
[ All Cheering ]

00:54:49.786 --> 00:54:53.873
HOW IN THE WORLD
DID OLD NOODLE-ARM PULL THAT OFF?

00:54:53.873 --> 00:54:56.208
AND WHO GETS THE CREDIT?

00:54:56.209 --> 00:54:59.712
GEORGE KNOX.
GEORGE KNOX.

00:55:01.921 --> 00:55:03.672
WE'RE DOWN IN THE ANGELS'
CLUBHOUSE FOR A TALK WITH MANAGER GEORGE KNOX.

00:55:03.673 --> 00:55:06.008
<i>WHAT INSPIRED YOU</i>
<i>TO START MEL?</i>

00:55:06.009 --> 00:55:08.928
A FEELING.  AN INSTINCT.
A KIND OF FAITH.

00:55:08.928 --> 00:55:12.431
A FAITH IN WHAT?
HAS MEL SHOWN THIS KIND OF POWER IN PRACTICE?

00:55:12.432 --> 00:55:15.935
MEL CLARK HAS ALWAYS
SHOWN HIMSELF TO BE AN EXTRAORDINARY ATHLETE.

00:55:15.935 --> 00:55:18.854
THE REST IS ABOUT BELIEVING
IN SOMETHING OR SOMEONE.

00:55:18.855 --> 00:55:21.190
NOW, WHEN DID YOU SUDDENLY
START BELIEVING IN CLARK?

00:55:21.191 --> 00:55:22.942
<i>HE'S BEEN SITTING</i>
<i>ON THE BENCH</i> <i>ALL SEASON.</i>

00:55:22.942 --> 00:55:26.445
[ Sighs ]
I LOOK FOR SIGNS. [ Player ]  IT'S GOOD TO WIN.

00:55:27.030 --> 00:55:29.365
[ Knox ]
SOMETIMES THEY COME FROM UNEXPECTED PLACES.

00:55:29.365 --> 00:55:31.116
LOOK, THAT'S ENOUGH
OUT OF ME FOR TODAY. UH-HUH.

00:55:31.117 --> 00:55:34.620
TALK TO THE STAR
OF THE GAME. EXCUSE ME.

00:55:34.621 --> 00:55:37.540
[ Crowd Murmuring ]

00:55:37.540 --> 00:55:41.043
SOMETHING'S GOING ON.

00:55:41.044 --> 00:55:43.379
MEL?  YOU TALK TO US
ABOUT THE GAME?

00:55:43.379 --> 00:55:46.298
WELL, IT--  IT FEELS GREAT
TO BE A WINNER AGAIN.

00:55:46.299 --> 00:55:49.135
WE WON!
YEAH. THREE IN A ROW.

00:55:49.135 --> 00:55:51.470
OH, I FEEL GOOD!

00:55:51.471 --> 00:55:55.558
- YEAH, ME TOO!
- ME THREE!

00:55:55.558 --> 00:55:57.893
[ Sighs ]
I OWE YOU GUYS.

00:55:57.894 --> 00:56:00.813
<i>OKAY, ANYTHING YOU WANT.</i>

00:56:00.813 --> 00:56:04.900
<i>YOU NAME IT.</i>
<i>YOU GOT IT.</i>

00:56:06.069 --> 00:56:07.820
ALL RIGHT,
LET'S PLAY BALL!

00:56:07.820 --> 00:56:10.155
[ Boys ]
YEAH!

00:56:10.156 --> 00:56:12.491
[ Boys Chattering ]

00:56:12.492 --> 00:56:15.995
COME ON, LET'S GO.
COME ON, LET'S GO.

00:56:15.995 --> 00:56:18.914
SLOW AND EASY.

00:56:18.915 --> 00:56:21.250
KEEP YOUR ELBOWS UP.

00:56:21.251 --> 00:56:23.002
HERE IT COMES.

00:56:23.002 --> 00:56:24.169
- <i>[ Boy ]  SWING HARD!</i>
<i>- [ Groans ]</i>

00:56:24.170 --> 00:56:27.089
GREAT HIT, J.P.!
[ Crowd Cheering ]

00:56:27.090 --> 00:56:29.425
[ Boy ]  GET IT, ROGER,
GET IT!  GET IT!

00:56:29.425 --> 00:56:31.760
YEAH!  ALL RIGHT!
[ Boy # 2 ]  ROGER, COME ON.

00:56:32.345 --> 00:56:33.512
YOU MISSED ON PURPOSE.
ALL RIGHT, J.P.!

00:56:33.513 --> 00:56:37.016
ALL RIGHT, WHO'S NEXT?
[ Boys Chanting "Me" ]

00:56:37.016 --> 00:56:41.103
<i>[ Knox ]</i>
<i>LET'S GIVE THE KID</i> <i>OVER ON THE CAR A SHOT.</i>

00:56:41.104 --> 00:56:44.607
[ Boys Groaning ]

00:56:44.607 --> 00:56:48.110
- WHAT'S YOUR NAME?
- MARVIN VINCENT ARCHER.

00:56:48.111 --> 00:56:51.614
YOU PLAY ANY BALL BEFORE,
MARVIN? NO, NEVER PLAYED ANY BALL.

00:56:51.614 --> 00:56:56.285
WELL, THIS IS
THE PERFECT TIME TO LEARN.  COME ON.

00:56:56.286 --> 00:57:00.373
[ Knox ]  WATCH THE BALL AND
WHEN I SAY, "NOW," YOU SWING. [ Boy ]  STAY SHARP, ZACK.

00:57:00.373 --> 00:57:02.708
<i>[ Knox ]</i>
<i>JUST DO EXACTLY</i> <i>WHAT I SAY.</i>

00:57:02.709 --> 00:57:05.044
<i>GET READY TO SWING.</i>

00:57:05.044 --> 00:57:07.963
NOW!  OH!  OH!
GO, MARVIN! RUN TO FIRST BASE!

00:57:08.548 --> 00:57:10.883
[ Crowd ]
GO, MARVIN, GO!

00:57:10.883 --> 00:57:13.802
[ Boy ]
YEAH!  YEAH!  THAT'S IT!

00:57:13.803 --> 00:57:18.474
- YOU STAY ON BASE
AND DO JUST WHAT I SAY. - OKAY.

00:57:19.058 --> 00:57:24.313
WE GOT RUNNERS
ON FIRST AND SECOND. [ Boy ]  PLACES NOW.

00:57:24.314 --> 00:57:29.569
[ Knox ]
AND LOOK WHO'S COMING TO BAT... BABE RUTH.

00:57:29.569 --> 00:57:33.072
[ Boys Chattering ]
<i>[ Thud, Glass Breaking ]</i>

00:57:33.072 --> 00:57:35.991
[ Growls ]

00:57:35.992 --> 00:57:38.911
[ Boy ]
GET READY.

00:57:38.911 --> 00:57:41.830
[ Batter Groans ]
OH!

00:57:41.831 --> 00:57:44.750
- <i>[ Boy ]  GO, MARVIN, GO!</i>
<i>- GO, MARVIN!  RUN HOME!</i>

00:57:44.751 --> 00:57:48.838
- RUN HOME?
RUN HOME.  RUN HOME. - RUN HOME!

00:57:48.838 --> 00:57:52.341
- RUN HOME.  RUN HOME.
- <i>[ Knox ]  HEY, MARVIN,</i> <i>WHERE YOU GOING?</i>

00:57:52.342 --> 00:57:55.845
- [ Laughing ]
- RUN HOME, RUN HOME, RUN HOME.

00:57:55.845 --> 00:57:58.764
HEY, WHERE'S HE GOIN'?
AND WHAT HAPPENED?

00:57:58.765 --> 00:58:01.100
YOU TOLD HIM TO RUN HOME.
HE DID. I--  I--

00:58:01.100 --> 00:58:04.603
[ Both Laughing ]

00:58:04.604 --> 00:58:08.691
[ Crowd Cheering ]

00:58:08.691 --> 00:58:10.442
[ Groans ]

00:58:12.195 --> 00:58:15.114
[ Crowd Cheering,
Whistling ]

00:58:15.114 --> 00:58:19.201
♪ [ "Take Me Out
To The Ball Game" ]

00:58:19.202 --> 00:58:21.537
[ Bat Cracking ]
♪ [ Organ Continues ]

00:58:21.537 --> 00:58:24.957
[ Crowd Applauds, Cheers ]

00:58:25.541 --> 00:58:27.876
[ Screaming ]

00:58:27.877 --> 00:58:31.964
[ Groans ]
[ Crowd Cheers ]

00:58:33.132 --> 00:58:35.467
[ Laughing ]
THAT'S COOL.

00:58:35.468 --> 00:58:39.555
[ Groans, Coughs ]
[ Laughing ] [ Laughing ]

00:58:39.555 --> 00:58:41.890
[ Crowd Booing ]
YOU CALL THAT A CALL? YOU CALL THAT A CALL?

00:58:41.891 --> 00:58:44.810
IN ALL MY YEARS OF BASEBALL,
I HAVE NEVER SEEN SUCH A--

00:58:44.811 --> 00:58:47.730
SUCH AN ASTUTE
EVALUATION...

00:58:47.730 --> 00:58:51.233
OF A POTENTIALLY
DIFFICULT DECISION.

00:58:51.818 --> 00:58:53.569
MASTERFUL CALL.

00:58:53.569 --> 00:58:56.488
OH, HAVE A NICE DAY.

00:58:56.489 --> 00:58:58.824
- [ Groans ]
- [ Pole Rattles ]

00:58:58.825 --> 00:59:02.328
[ Ball Thuds,
Crowd Cheers ] FAIR BALL!

00:59:02.328 --> 00:59:06.415
- [ Grunts ]
- [ Panting ]

00:59:06.416 --> 00:59:08.751
- [ Slap ]
- OW!

00:59:08.751 --> 00:59:12.254
- [ Crowd Cheering ]
- [ Panting ]

00:59:12.255 --> 00:59:16.342
- [ Slap ]
- [ Screaming ]

00:59:18.094 --> 00:59:20.429
SAFE!
YEAH!

00:59:21.597 --> 00:59:23.932
YAHOO!
[ Slapping ]

00:59:23.933 --> 00:59:26.268
- YEAH!
- YEAH, YEAH, YEAH, YEAH!

00:59:26.269 --> 00:59:28.604
[ Crowd Cheering ]

00:59:32.108 --> 00:59:33.859
YES!
THERE YOU GO, PAL.

00:59:34.444 --> 00:59:36.195
THANKS!
ALL RIGHT. OH, THANKS, MEL.

00:59:36.195 --> 00:59:38.530
HEY, THAT'S MY BALL.
OH, IT'S--

00:59:44.370 --> 00:59:46.121
[ Players Shouting ]

00:59:46.122 --> 00:59:49.041
UNBELIEVABLE!

00:59:54.881 --> 00:59:57.800
GET OUT OF THE WAY!
[ Groans ]

00:59:57.800 --> 01:00:00.135
[ Crowd Cheering ]
[ Groans ]

01:00:04.223 --> 01:00:07.142
[ Cheering ]

01:00:10.646 --> 01:00:12.981
[ Groans ]

01:00:18.237 --> 01:00:21.156
- YOU'RE OUTTA HERE!
- YEAH!

01:00:21.741 --> 01:00:24.076
- ♪ [ Crowd Singing "Take Me
Out To The Ball Game" ] - NO?

01:00:24.076 --> 01:00:26.411
♪ [ Singing Continues ]

01:00:26.412 --> 01:00:28.747
- HEY!
- ♪ BUY ME SOME PEANUTS AND CRACKER JACK ♪

01:00:28.748 --> 01:00:32.835
♪ I DON'T CARE
IF I NEVER GET BACK ♪

01:00:33.419 --> 01:00:36.338
♪ SO IT'S ROOT, ROOT, ROOT
FOR THE HOME TEAM ♪

01:00:36.339 --> 01:00:40.426
♪ IF THEY DON'T WIN
IT'S A SHAME ♪

01:00:40.426 --> 01:00:42.177
[ Crowd Cheering ]
♪ FOR IT'S ONE, TWO ♪

01:00:42.762 --> 01:00:47.433
♪ THREE STRIKES YOU'RE OUT
AT THE OLD BALL GAME ♪

01:00:47.433 --> 01:00:50.352
[ Crowd Cheering ]
GO!

01:00:50.353 --> 01:00:52.688
[ Slap ]

01:00:52.688 --> 01:00:55.023
[ Slap ]

01:00:55.024 --> 01:01:00.112
[ Crowd Cheering,
Applause ]

01:01:00.112 --> 01:01:01.863
[ Wilder ]
THE ANGELS HAVE CLOSED OUT THE SEASON...

01:01:02.448 --> 01:01:04.783
WITH AN INCREDIBLE
HOT STREAK.

01:01:05.368 --> 01:01:08.287
WHO WOULD HAVE BELIEVED THIS
TEAM COULD GO FROM LAST PLACE AT THE ALL-STAR BREAK...

01:01:08.287 --> 01:01:11.206
TO JUST ONE WIN AWAY
FROM CLINCHING THE DIVISION TITLE?

01:01:11.207 --> 01:01:13.542
NOW IT ALL COMES DOWN
TO THE LAST TWO GAMES OF THE SEASON.

01:01:13.543 --> 01:01:18.214
AND, IRONICALLY, THEY ARE
WITH THE DEFENDING CHAMPION, CHICAGO WHITE SOX...

01:01:18.214 --> 01:01:20.549
WHO ARE ONE GAME BACK
AND CLOSING FAST IN A DETERMINED EFFORT...

01:01:20.550 --> 01:01:24.637
TO DENY THE ANGELS
THE CHAMPIONSHIP. [ Electronic Whirring ]

01:01:24.637 --> 01:01:29.308
THE FIRST OF THOSE CRUCIAL
GAMES TAKES PLACE RIGHT HERE...

01:01:29.308 --> 01:01:31.643
THIS AFTERNOON.

01:01:34.564 --> 01:01:36.899
WHAT'S IT SAY?

01:01:36.899 --> 01:01:38.650
THANKS.  'BYE.
[ Roger ]  SAYS THE VAN'S GONNA PICK US UP AT 12:00.

01:01:38.651 --> 01:01:40.986
ROGER?  STUPID THING.
[ Dial Tone Beeping ]

01:01:40.987 --> 01:01:43.322
ROGER?  THAT WAS
YOUR SOCIAL WORKER. [ Roger ]  HUH?

01:01:43.322 --> 01:01:48.577
WHAT DID SHE WANT?
<i>YOUR HEARING'S BEEN CHANGED</i> <i>TO THIS AFTERNOON.</i>

01:01:48.578 --> 01:01:51.497
- BUT I GOT A GAME
THIS AFTERNOON. - I KNOW.

01:01:51.497 --> 01:01:55.584
I'VE JUST TRIED EVERYTHING
TO GET THEM TO RESCHEDULE. IT'S JUST NOT POSSIBLE.

01:01:55.585 --> 01:01:57.920
MAGGIE, I'M NOT GOING.

01:01:57.920 --> 01:02:02.007
YOU DON'T HAVE A CHOICE,
SWEETHEART.

01:02:02.008 --> 01:02:05.511
- WELL, WHAT ABOUT GEORGE?
WHAT ABOUT THE ANGELS-- - I'LL CALL MR. KNOX.

01:02:06.095 --> 01:02:07.846
I KNOW HE THINKS YOU GUYS
ARE HIS LUCKY CHARMS...

01:02:07.847 --> 01:02:10.766
<i>BUT THIS IS JUST</i>
<i>SOMETHING YOU HAVE TO DO.</i>

01:02:10.766 --> 01:02:13.101
[ Roger Sighs ]
J.P. CAN GO TO THE GAME...

01:02:13.102 --> 01:02:16.605
AND WE'LL JUST TRY REAL HARD
TO GET YOU THERE BEFORE IT'S OVER.

01:02:16.606 --> 01:02:18.357
THAT'S ALL I CAN DO.

01:02:18.941 --> 01:02:23.028
OH, MAN!
[ Sighs ] WHAT ABOUT THE GAME?

01:02:23.029 --> 01:02:27.116
[ Announcer ]
ATTENTION YOUNGSTERS, AGED SIX TO 16.

01:02:27.116 --> 01:02:30.035
BE SURE TO JOIN
THE JUNIOR ANGEL FAN CLUB.

01:02:30.036 --> 01:02:34.707
FOR JUST $5.00, YOU'LL RECEIVE
GAME TICKETS, BASEBALL CARDS, A FREE AUTOGRAPHED--

01:02:34.707 --> 01:02:37.042
[ Wilder ]
THE SOUTHERN CALIFORNIA SUN IS SHINING;

01:02:37.043 --> 01:02:39.962
THE FIELD IS READY,
THE HOT DOGS ARE WARM...

01:02:39.962 --> 01:02:44.049
AND THERE'S NOT AN EMPTY SEAT
IN THE HOUSE. [ Creaking ]

01:02:44.050 --> 01:02:46.385
[ Vendor ]
GET YOUR HOT DOGS!

01:02:46.385 --> 01:02:48.720
I KNOW.  I KNOW.
DON'T EVEN SAY IT.

01:02:48.721 --> 01:02:51.056
A LARGE COKE, TWO DOGS,
THREE CRACKER JACKS.

01:02:51.057 --> 01:02:53.392
AND I WAS THINKING
OF GETTING HIM A CAR. AND MAYBE A CORPORATE JET--

01:02:53.392 --> 01:02:57.479
STILL NO ROGER.
HE'LL BE HERE ANY SECOND.

01:02:57.480 --> 01:03:00.399
OF ALL THE DAYS
TO HAUL THE KID OFF TO COURT.

01:03:00.399 --> 01:03:02.734
WHY DIDN'T MAGGIE SAY
HE WAS SICK OR SOMETHING?

01:03:02.735 --> 01:03:05.654
THAT'D BE LYING.
MAGGIE WOULD NEVER LIE.

01:03:06.238 --> 01:03:09.157
WELL, MAGGIE'S NOT
IN A PENNANT RACE.

01:03:09.158 --> 01:03:12.661
[ Announcer ]
NUMBER 19, THIRD BASEMAN, BRUCE SHEA.

01:03:14.413 --> 01:03:19.668
HEY, YOU DON'T SEE ANYTHING,
DO YOU? MAYBE.

01:03:25.508 --> 01:03:27.843
HMM?

01:03:32.515 --> 01:03:34.850
SORRY.

01:03:34.850 --> 01:03:38.353
OH, IT'S NOT YOUR FAULT.

01:03:38.354 --> 01:03:40.689
YOU NEVER SEEN
ANGELS BEFORE.

01:03:40.690 --> 01:03:45.361
WHY SHOULD YOU NOW?
HEY, IT COULD HAPPEN.

01:04:00.543 --> 01:04:02.294
[ Sighs ]

01:04:02.294 --> 01:04:04.045
YOU UNDERSTAND THAT
ONCE THIS HEARING...

01:04:04.046 --> 01:04:06.965
HAS ESTABLISHED ROGER'S
PERMANENT PLACEMENT STATUS...

01:04:06.966 --> 01:04:12.805
HIS WELFARE WILL FOREVER FORWARD
BE DETERMINED BY THIS COURT?

01:04:12.805 --> 01:04:18.060
I UNDERSTAND.
AND YOU'VE CONSULTED A LAWYER?

01:04:18.644 --> 01:04:21.563
LOOK, LADY,
I GET WHAT I'M DOING. THE KID'S NOT MINE ANYMORE.

01:04:21.564 --> 01:04:23.899
I'M NOT PROUD OF IT.

01:04:24.483 --> 01:04:27.402
IT'S NOT SOMETHING I CAN
CHANGE MY MIND ABOUT EITHER.

01:04:30.906 --> 01:04:34.993
WE'RE READY
TO SEE YOU NOW, ROGER.

01:04:34.994 --> 01:04:37.329
[ Sighs ]

01:04:43.753 --> 01:04:46.088
DAD?

01:04:46.088 --> 01:04:49.007
DAD, I DIDN'T KNOW
YOU WERE GOING TO BE HERE.

01:04:49.008 --> 01:04:53.095
YOU KNOW, THE ANGELS ARE ONLY
ONE GAME FROM THE PENNANT? CAN YOU BELIEVE IT?

01:04:53.679 --> 01:04:56.598
<i>IT'S JUST LIKE</i>
<i>YOU SAID.</i>

01:04:58.934 --> 01:05:02.437
SORRY, BOY.
DAD?

01:05:02.438 --> 01:05:07.693
HEY, DAD, WH--
DID YOU HEAR WHAT I SAID?

01:05:07.693 --> 01:05:11.780
<i>WHERE ARE YOU GOING?</i>

01:05:11.781 --> 01:05:14.116
DADDY?

01:05:21.707 --> 01:05:24.042
DON'T CRY.
COME BACK.

01:05:24.043 --> 01:05:29.298
[ Sobbing ]

01:05:29.882 --> 01:05:31.633
[ Crowd Booing ]

01:05:38.057 --> 01:05:39.808
WE LOST.
[ Sobbing ] DON'T CRY.

01:05:40.392 --> 01:05:44.479
IT-IT'S ONLY A GAME.
COME ON, YOU'RE GETTING SNOT ALL OVER THE PLACE.

01:05:44.480 --> 01:05:46.815
- IT'S NOBODY'S FAULT.
- I TRIED TO SEE ANGELS.

01:05:46.816 --> 01:05:49.151
[ J.P. ]
I REALLY TRIED.

01:05:49.151 --> 01:05:51.486
I GUESS,
WITHOUT ANGELS HELPING,

01:05:51.487 --> 01:05:53.822
THIS TEAM DOESN'T
HAVE WHAT IT TAKES.

01:05:54.406 --> 01:05:57.909
OR MAYBE I JUST DON'T
HAVE WHAT IT TAKES.

01:05:57.910 --> 01:06:01.413
WE COULD STILL WIN
WITHOUT THE ANGELS. IT COULD HAPPEN.

01:06:01.413 --> 01:06:03.748
MAYBE.

01:06:03.749 --> 01:06:06.668
UH, GIVE ME A MINUTE, KID,
AND I'LL BE OUT TO TAKE YOU HOME.

01:06:06.669 --> 01:06:08.420
DON'T CRY.

01:06:08.420 --> 01:06:12.507
[ Man ]
NO, WE'RE NOT.

01:06:16.011 --> 01:06:17.762
[ Man #2 ]
HEY, PUT OUT THAT CIGARETTE.

01:06:17.763 --> 01:06:21.850
[ Door Shuts ]
HEY.

01:06:21.851 --> 01:06:25.354
I'M RANCH WILDER,

01:06:25.354 --> 01:06:28.857
THE VOICE OF THE ANGELS.

01:06:28.858 --> 01:06:32.945
I KNOW WHO YOU ARE.
I HEARD YOU ON THE RADIO.

01:06:32.945 --> 01:06:36.448
YOU SURE DO
HAVE A BIG CHIN.

01:06:36.448 --> 01:06:39.367
EVERYBODY'S A CRITIC.

01:06:39.952 --> 01:06:41.703
SO WHAT'S YOUR NAME?

01:06:41.704 --> 01:06:45.207
J.P.
WELL, J.P., THAT WAS A TOUGH LOSS TODAY, HUH?

01:06:45.791 --> 01:06:48.710
KNOX TOOK IT PRETTY HARD.
HE WAS GETTING KIND OF CRAZY OUT THERE.

01:06:49.295 --> 01:06:51.630
- 'CAUSE ROGER COULDN'T COME.
- I GET IT.

01:06:51.630 --> 01:06:53.965
SO ROGER'S SORT OF LUCKY.
IS THAT IT?

01:06:53.966 --> 01:06:58.637
HE SEES THE ANGELS,
THE ONES WHO HELP OUT. HE PRAYED FOR 'EM.

01:06:58.637 --> 01:07:04.476
- REAL ANGELS?
- YEAH, BUT, I DON'T SEE 'EM.

01:07:04.476 --> 01:07:08.563
AND KNOX, HE SEES THEM?

01:07:08.564 --> 01:07:13.235
NO.  ROGER HAS TO TELL HIM
WHEN THEY'RE AROUND.

01:07:13.235 --> 01:07:15.570
REALLY?

01:07:19.074 --> 01:07:21.409
[ Maggie ]
YOU KNOW, BY RELEASING YOU LEGALLY,

01:07:21.410 --> 01:07:24.913
IT DOES MAKE IT
POSSIBLE FOR SOMEBODY TO TAKE YOU PERMANENTLY.

01:07:24.914 --> 01:07:28.417
HE DID THAT 'CAUSE HE
WANTS THE BEST FOR YOU.

01:07:28.417 --> 01:07:32.504
YEAH.  GIVING SOMEONE AWAY
IS A GREAT WAY TO SHOW 'IM YOU CARE.

01:07:37.176 --> 01:07:38.927
[ Chassis Squeaks ]

01:07:38.928 --> 01:07:42.431
<i>[ Engine Stops ]</i>
<i>HEY, ROGER.</i>

01:07:42.431 --> 01:07:44.766
TOOK A LITTLE LONGER
THAN YOU EXPECTED. <i>[ Car Door Opens, Shuts ]</i>

01:07:44.767 --> 01:07:47.102
WE WAITED THREE HOURS
FOR HIS HEARING.

01:07:47.102 --> 01:07:49.437
THAT'S QUICK
FOR FAMILY COURT.

01:07:49.438 --> 01:07:52.941
WHAT'D THEY DECIDE?
OH, IT'S JUST A FORMALITY.

01:07:54.693 --> 01:07:59.364
HE BELONGS TO THE STATE
OF CALIFORNIA NOW.

01:07:59.365 --> 01:08:01.700
[ Sighs ]
SCOOT OVER.

01:08:01.700 --> 01:08:05.203
[ Sighs ]

01:08:08.123 --> 01:08:10.458
[ Exhales Loudly ]

01:08:13.963 --> 01:08:16.882
ROGER, I'M SORRY
ABOUT TODAY.

01:08:16.882 --> 01:08:21.553
WHY?  BECAUSE YOU LOST
YOUR STUPID BASEBALL GAME?

01:08:21.553 --> 01:08:23.888
NO, BECAUSE
YOU'RE HURT.

01:08:23.889 --> 01:08:26.808
[ Sighs ]
YOU DON'T KNOW ANYTHING ABOUT IT.

01:08:32.064 --> 01:08:34.983
YOU KNOW, ROGER,
WHEN I WAS GROWING UP,

01:08:34.984 --> 01:08:37.903
I NEVER SAW VERY MUCH
OF MY DAD.

01:08:37.903 --> 01:08:40.822
<i>HE COULDN'T TAKE</i>
<i>CARE OF HIMSELF...</i>

01:08:40.823 --> 01:08:43.158
<i>SO TAKING CARE OF ME</i>
<i>AND MY BROTHERS...</i>

01:08:43.158 --> 01:08:46.661
<i>WAS OUT</i>
<i>OF THE QUESTION.</i>

01:08:48.414 --> 01:08:53.669
I'M NOT SURE THE PAIN
THAT CAUSED EVER GOES AWAY.

01:08:53.669 --> 01:08:57.756
BUT I AM SURE
YOU CAN'T GO THROUGH LIFE...

01:08:57.756 --> 01:09:01.843
THINKING EVERYONE YOU MEET
WILL ONE DAY LET YOU DOWN.

01:09:01.844 --> 01:09:07.099
BECAUSE, IF YOU DO,
A VERY BAD THING WILL HAPPEN.

01:09:07.099 --> 01:09:09.434
<i>[ Sighs ]</i>

01:09:09.435 --> 01:09:12.354
YOU'LL END UP LIKE ME.

01:09:15.274 --> 01:09:18.777
I'M GOING INSIDE.
<i>[ Hinges Squeak ]</i>

01:09:18.777 --> 01:09:23.448
I THOUGHT YOU SAID
YOU HAD TO BE SOMEWHERE.

01:09:23.449 --> 01:09:26.368
I DO.
RIGHT HERE.

01:09:26.368 --> 01:09:30.455
- YUCK!
- YOU BOTH WASH YOUR HANDS?

01:09:30.456 --> 01:09:34.543
<i>YEAH.</i>
<i>OKAY THEN,</i> <i>LET'S DIG IN.</i>

01:09:34.543 --> 01:09:35.710
[ Chuckles ]

01:09:35.711 --> 01:09:38.630
NEXT TIME
I'LL TRY LASAGNA.

01:09:38.630 --> 01:09:40.965
YOU GUYS LIKE LASAGNA?

01:09:40.966 --> 01:09:44.469
NO.  WHAT IS IT?
NO.  WHAT IS IT?

01:09:44.470 --> 01:09:48.557
LOOK!
IT'S GOD'S THUMBNAIL.

01:09:48.557 --> 01:09:52.060
THAT'S JUST
THE MOON, J.P.

01:09:52.061 --> 01:09:54.396
NO GOD UP THERE.

01:09:54.980 --> 01:09:58.483
[ Crickets Chirping ]

01:09:59.068 --> 01:10:02.571
I CAN'T BELIEVE
YOU SAID THAT.

01:10:02.571 --> 01:10:06.658
THE KID WHO SEES ANGELS?

01:10:06.658 --> 01:10:10.161
I DON'T BELIEVE
IN ANGELS ANYMORE.

01:10:10.162 --> 01:10:14.833
- ROGER, WHAT ARE YOU
TALKING ABOUT? - THAT'S OKAY, J.P.

01:10:14.833 --> 01:10:17.752
ROGER'S HAD A TOUGH DAY.

01:10:28.263 --> 01:10:30.014
[ Sighs ]

01:10:40.275 --> 01:10:42.610
<i>[ Door Shuts ]</i>

01:10:44.363 --> 01:10:47.866
"THE SOURCE SAYS THERE'S A BOY
KNOWN AS ROGER...

01:10:47.866 --> 01:10:52.537
"WHO EVEN WATCHES GAMES ON TV
WHEN THE TEAM IS OUT OF TOWN...

01:10:52.538 --> 01:10:54.873
AND REPORTS TO MANAGER KNOX
OVER THE PHONE."

01:10:54.873 --> 01:10:57.208
WHAT'S A SOURCE?

01:10:57.793 --> 01:11:00.712
THE PERSON
WHO TOLD. OH.

01:11:00.712 --> 01:11:03.047
"AND WHEN MEL CLARK MADE HIS
AMAZING COMEBACK IN AUGUST,

01:11:03.048 --> 01:11:05.967
IT WAS ROGER'S, IT WAS ROGER'S
IDEA TO START HIM."

01:11:05.968 --> 01:11:10.055
- THAT'S ME.
- WHO DO YOU THINK TOLD?

01:11:10.055 --> 01:11:12.390
I DON'T KNOW.

01:11:12.391 --> 01:11:15.310
MAYBE DAVID FOUND OUT.
I DON'T SEE HOW. ARE WE IN TROUBLE?

01:11:15.894 --> 01:11:17.645
KNOX IS IN TROUBLE
AND THAT'S FOR SURE.

01:11:17.646 --> 01:11:19.981
THIS IS BAD.  RIGHT?

01:11:19.982 --> 01:11:22.901
WE'RE GONNA HAVE
TO TELL MAGGIE.

01:11:24.069 --> 01:11:26.404
[ Sighs ]

01:11:26.405 --> 01:11:30.492
[ Woman ]
RIGHT THIS WAY, MR. KNOX.

01:11:30.492 --> 01:11:33.411
YOU STOOD ME UP
LAST NIGHT.

01:11:33.412 --> 01:11:37.499
WHAT IN THE SAM HILL
IS ALL THIS ABOUT REAL ANGELS?

01:11:37.499 --> 01:11:40.418
- IT'S NOTHING.
- START TALKIN'!

01:11:40.419 --> 01:11:43.922
OKAY, I--
I GOT THESE TWO KIDS...

01:11:43.922 --> 01:11:48.009
AND I THINK OF THEM
AS MASCOTS.

01:11:48.010 --> 01:11:52.097
AND... THE ANGELS,
UH, WELL...

01:11:52.097 --> 01:11:56.184
IT'S JUST SOMETHING
THAT'S GOING ON BETWEEN ME AND THEM.

01:11:56.185 --> 01:11:57.936
YOU'RE TELLING ME,
THERE'S REAL ANGELS IN THE BALLPARK?

01:11:57.936 --> 01:12:01.439
SOMETIMES,
BUT THEY'RE NOT IN ON ALL THE PLAYS.

01:12:01.440 --> 01:12:03.775
[ Chuckles ]
YOU'VE LOST IT, PARDNER.

01:12:03.775 --> 01:12:09.030
LOOK, IF I LIED TO YOU,
THEN THE ANGELS WOULDN'T LIKE IT AND THEY MIGHT NOT COME BACK.

01:12:09.031 --> 01:12:13.702
THEY'RE VERY...
TEMPERAMENTAL.

01:12:14.286 --> 01:12:16.037
"MENTAL" IS THE KEY WORD HERE.

01:12:16.038 --> 01:12:19.541
I'M SORRY, GEORGE,
BUT I'M RELIEVING YOU...

01:12:19.541 --> 01:12:21.876
OF YOUR MANAGEMENT
RESPONSIBILITIES.

01:12:21.877 --> 01:12:24.212
YOU CAN'T DO THAT.

01:12:24.213 --> 01:12:26.548
<i>WE'RE ONLY</i>
<i>ONE GAME AWAY.</i>

01:12:26.548 --> 01:12:28.883
I'LL TELL YOU WHAT.

01:12:28.884 --> 01:12:31.803
I'LL GIVE YOU 24 HOURS
TO GET YOUR HEAD ON STRAIGHT.

01:12:31.803 --> 01:12:34.138
THEN I'LL CALL
A PRESS CONFERENCE...

01:12:34.139 --> 01:12:37.642
AND YOU CAN PUBLICLY
RENOUNCE THIS HOGWASH.

01:12:37.643 --> 01:12:43.482
GEORGE, YOU REPEAT
ANY OF THE BALONEY I'VE HEARD HERE,

01:12:43.482 --> 01:12:46.985
WE'RE TALKING THE END
OF YOUR CAREER IN BASEBALL.

01:12:46.985 --> 01:12:52.240
HAVE I MADE MYSELF CLEAR?
YES.

01:12:59.248 --> 01:13:02.167
[ Rustling Papers ]

01:13:20.852 --> 01:13:25.523
[ Crowd Clamoring ]

01:13:26.108 --> 01:13:29.611
[ Reporter ]
WHAT'S GOING ON, KNOX? WHAT'S GOING ON?

01:13:29.611 --> 01:13:33.114
[ Clamoring Subsides ]
GOOD MORNING, LADIES AND GENTLEMEN.

01:13:33.115 --> 01:13:35.450
<i>WE'RE GONNA MAKE THIS</i>
<i>SHORT AND SWEET.</i>

01:13:36.034 --> 01:13:40.121
MY MANAGER, GEORGE KNOX HERE,
HAS SOMETHING HE'D LIKE TO SAY TO YOU.  GEORGE?

01:13:40.122 --> 01:13:44.209
I HAVE A STATEMENT
I'D LIKE TO READ.

01:13:44.209 --> 01:13:49.464
"THERE HAVE BEEN REPORTS
THAT I'VE BEEN USING ANGELS...

01:13:49.464 --> 01:13:52.967
<i>TO HELP THE TEAM WIN."</i>

01:13:53.552 --> 01:13:56.471
[ Maggie ]
GO ON.  GO IN.

01:13:56.471 --> 01:14:00.558
[ Crowd Murmuring ]

01:14:08.150 --> 01:14:11.653
[ Sighs ]

01:14:11.653 --> 01:14:15.740
I WAS GONNA READ
A STATEMENT...

01:14:15.741 --> 01:14:20.996
BUT, INSTEAD,
I'M GONNA SHOOT FROM THE HIP.

01:14:23.332 --> 01:14:29.171
YOU KNOW, THERE ARE A LOT
OF TIMES IN SPORTS...

01:14:29.171 --> 01:14:34.426
WHEN THERE'S
NO LOGICAL EXPLANATION WHY THINGS HAPPEN.

01:14:34.426 --> 01:14:37.929
<i>SOMETIMES A PLAYER</i>
<i>GETS HOT...</i>

01:14:38.513 --> 01:14:41.432
AND GOES BEYOND
THEIR PHYSICAL ABILITY.

01:14:41.433 --> 01:14:45.520
<i>IS IT JUST ADRENALINE?</i>
<i>I DON'T KNOW.</i>

01:14:45.520 --> 01:14:49.023
BUT, I DO BELIEVE
THERE ARE TIMES IN LIFE...

01:14:49.608 --> 01:14:53.111
WHERE SOMETHING STRONGER,
HIGHER,

01:14:53.111 --> 01:14:56.030
OR MAYBE SPIRITUAL
IS WITH US.

01:14:56.031 --> 01:14:58.950
I CAN'T EXPLAIN IT,
BUT SOMETHING HAS HAPPENED...

01:14:58.950 --> 01:15:00.701
TO MY PLAYERS THIS YEAR.

01:15:00.702 --> 01:15:05.373
SOMETHING THAT'S CHANGED
THE WAY THEY PLAY...

01:15:05.374 --> 01:15:08.877
AND THE WAY I MANAGE.

01:15:08.877 --> 01:15:12.380
<i>YOU CAN CALL IT FAITH.</i>
<i>YOU CAN CALL IT ANGELS.</i>

01:15:12.381 --> 01:15:15.884
YOU CAN CALL IT
WHATEVER YOU WANT.

01:15:15.884 --> 01:15:18.803
THAT'S ALL
I HAVE TO SAY.

01:15:19.388 --> 01:15:22.891
GEORGE, DOES THIS MEAN
YOU REALLY THINK...

01:15:22.891 --> 01:15:26.394
THAT A KID SEES ANGELS
AT YOUR GAMES?

01:15:26.978 --> 01:15:28.729
[ Crowd Murmuring ]

01:15:28.730 --> 01:15:30.481
[ Clears Throat ]
EXCUSE ME.

01:15:30.482 --> 01:15:33.401
I'D, UH, I'D LIKE
TO SAY SOMETHING...

01:15:33.402 --> 01:15:35.737
ON BEHALF
OF GEORGE KNOX.

01:15:35.737 --> 01:15:38.072
UH, WHAT'S YOUR NAME?
WHAT'S YOUR BUSINESS HERE?

01:15:38.073 --> 01:15:43.912
MY NAME IS MAGGIE NELSON.
I TAKE CARE OF FOSTER KIDS.

01:15:43.912 --> 01:15:47.415
ONE OF THESE BOYS IS, UH,
THE CHILD WHO CAN SEE ANGELS.

01:15:47.416 --> 01:15:52.087
<i>HE COULD STAND UP RIGHT NOW</i>
<i>AND TELL YOU EXACTLY</i> <i>WHAT'S HAPPENED...</i>

01:15:52.087 --> 01:15:54.422
AND I KNOW YOU'D
JUST LAUGH AT HIM.

01:15:54.423 --> 01:15:57.342
BUT, WHEN A PROFESSIONAL
FOOTBALL PLAYER...

01:15:57.342 --> 01:16:02.013
DROPS TO ONE KNEE TO THANK GOD
AFTER MAKING A TOUCHDOWN, NOBODY LAUGHS AT THAT.

01:16:02.013 --> 01:16:07.268
OR WHEN A PITCHER CROSSES
HIMSELF BEFORE GOING TO THE MOUND, NOBODY LAUGHS AT THAT.

01:16:07.269 --> 01:16:12.524
SEEMS LIKE YOU'RE SAYING IT'S
OKAY TO BELIEVE IN GOD, BUT IT'S NOT OKAY TO BELIEVE IN ANGELS.

01:16:13.108 --> 01:16:14.859
NOW, I THOUGHT THEY WERE
ON THE SAME TEAM.

01:16:14.860 --> 01:16:18.947
IS IT YOUR BELIEF,
MA'AM, THAT, UH, ANGELS PLAY BASEBALL?

01:16:18.947 --> 01:16:22.450
SINCE THE
ALL-STAR BREAK, YES!

01:16:22.451 --> 01:16:26.538
[ Crowd Laughing ]

01:16:26.538 --> 01:16:29.457
WE ALL NEED SOMEBODY
TO WATCH OUT FOR US.

01:16:29.458 --> 01:16:32.377
<i>EVERY KID I HAVE</i>
<i>EVER TAKEN CARE OF...</i>

01:16:32.377 --> 01:16:36.464
HAS BEEN LOOKING FOR SOMEONE
TO LOVE: AN ANGEL.

01:16:36.465 --> 01:16:42.304
YOU'VE GOT TO HAVE FAITH.
YOU'VE GOT TO BELIEVE.

01:16:42.304 --> 01:16:44.639
YOU'VE GOT TO LOOK
INSIDE YOURSELF.

01:16:44.639 --> 01:16:47.558
THE FOOTPRINTS
OF AN ANGEL <i>ARE</i> LOVE.

01:16:47.559 --> 01:16:51.646
AND WHERE THERE IS LOVE,
MIRACULOUS THINGS CAN HAPPEN.

01:16:52.230 --> 01:16:54.565
I'VE SEEN IT.

01:16:55.150 --> 01:16:57.485
I'D ALSO LIKE
TO SAY SOMETHING.

01:16:59.237 --> 01:17:02.156
I DON'T KNOW IF THERE
ARE ANGELS OUT THERE...

01:17:02.157 --> 01:17:06.244
OTHER THAN THE 25
OF US IN UNIFORM.

01:17:06.828 --> 01:17:08.579
BUT I KNOW
THERE IS ONE THING I WON'T DO.

01:17:08.580 --> 01:17:13.835
I WON'T PLAY FOR ANYONE
BUT GEORGE KNOX. I BELIEVE IN HIM.

01:17:13.835 --> 01:17:15.586
[ Crowd Murmuring ]

01:17:18.507 --> 01:17:20.842
THAT GOES FOR ME TOO.

01:17:36.608 --> 01:17:39.527
[#
THANK YOU. ALL OF YOU.

01:17:43.615 --> 01:17:46.534
<i>[ Murphy ]</i>
<i>PRINT WHAT YOU WANT.</i>

01:17:46.535 --> 01:17:50.622
- GEORGE KNOX <i>IS</i> THE MANAGER
OF THE BALL CLUB. - [ Cheering ]

01:17:50.622 --> 01:17:56.461
AND, IF THERE ARE ANY ANGELS
OUT THERE, I SURE HOPE THEY'RE ON OUR SIDE.

01:17:59.965 --> 01:18:02.884
- OH, YEAH!
- YEAH!  YES!

01:18:09.140 --> 01:18:12.643
[ Wilder ]  GOOD EVENING,
EVERYONE, AND WELCOME TO DOWNTOWN ANAHEIM...

01:18:12.644 --> 01:18:14.979
WHERE THERE ARE NO SEATS LEFT
IN SPORTS HEAVEN...

01:18:15.564 --> 01:18:19.067
AS A SELLOUT CROWD FILLS
THE BALLPARK FOR THE FINAL GAME OF THE SEASON.

01:18:19.067 --> 01:18:22.570
TONIGHT, GEORGE KNOX
WILL SEND HIS ANGELS,

01:18:22.571 --> 01:18:26.074
REAL OR IMAGINED, OUT AGAINST
A TOUGH WHITE SOX TEAM...

01:18:26.658 --> 01:18:30.161
TO DETERMINE WHO WILL BE
THE WESTERN DIVISION CHAMPION.

01:18:30.161 --> 01:18:33.080
WHEN I CAME HERE THIS SEASON,
I DIDN'T BELIEVE IN YOU GUYS.

01:18:33.081 --> 01:18:35.416
<i>I DIDN'T BELIEVE</i>
<i>IN ANYTHING.</i>

01:18:35.417 --> 01:18:40.088
BUT, WHEN YOU STOOD UP
THIS MORNING, YOU GAVE ME BACK MY REASON TO BELIEVE.

01:18:40.088 --> 01:18:43.591
I'M MORE PROUD
OF BEING A PART OF THIS TEAM THAN ANY TEAM I'VE BEEN ON.

01:18:43.592 --> 01:18:46.511
YOU'RE ALL WINNERS
AND I BELIEVE IN YOU!

01:18:46.511 --> 01:18:50.014
SO LET'S GO OUT THERE AND SHOW
THEM WHAT WINNERS CAN DO!

01:18:50.015 --> 01:18:52.350
LET'S TAKE THAT
CHAMPIONSHIP! [ All ]  YEAH!

01:18:52.350 --> 01:18:56.437
YEAH!  ALL RIGHT!
YOU LOOK FANTASTIC!

01:18:56.438 --> 01:18:58.773
OKAY, YOU HEARD HIM.
LET'S GO!

01:18:59.357 --> 01:19:02.860
[ Announcer ]
LADIES AND GENTLEMEN, YOUR CALIFORNIA ANGELS!

01:19:02.861 --> 01:19:08.116
[ Crowd Cheering ]

01:19:08.116 --> 01:19:11.035
[ Wilder ]
STARTING PITCHER FOR THE ANGELS IN THIS CRUCIAL GAME...

01:19:11.036 --> 01:19:13.371
IS THE VETERAN MEL CLARK.

01:19:13.371 --> 01:19:15.122
YEAH!
ALL RIGHT!

01:19:15.123 --> 01:19:19.794
HE'S BEEN THEIR BIG-GAME GUY
SINCE HE RETURNED TO THE LINEUP IN JULY.

01:19:19.794 --> 01:19:22.713
SO CLARK'S HAD A ROCKY START
HERE IN THE FIRST.

01:19:22.714 --> 01:19:26.801
HE'S GOT RUNNERS ON SECOND
AND THIRD WITH TWO OUTS AND DARREN AT BAT.

01:19:26.801 --> 01:19:29.720
[ Crowd Chattering ]

01:19:29.721 --> 01:19:32.056
[ Groans ]

01:19:32.057 --> 01:19:34.392
DARREN DRIVES THE BALL
TO LEFT.

01:19:34.392 --> 01:19:36.727
IT'S FAIR!
ONE RUN WILL SCORE AND HERE COMES COOPER!

01:19:36.728 --> 01:19:40.231
NORTON GETS TO IT.
IT'S GONNA BE CLOSE. HERE COMES THE BALL!

01:19:40.231 --> 01:19:43.150
COOPER SLIDES.
HE'S SAFE!

01:19:43.151 --> 01:19:47.238
THE FANS DON'T LIKE THE CALL,
BUT THE SOX GO UP 2-0 AND WE'RE STILL IN THE TOP OF THE FIRST.

01:19:47.238 --> 01:19:49.573
YOU GOT 'IM NOW!
GO, GO, YEAH! [ Sighs ]

01:19:49.574 --> 01:19:53.077
[ Wilder ]
CLARK PITCHES TO YOUNG. [ Groans ]

01:19:53.078 --> 01:19:55.997
HE LOOPS ONE OVER SECOND BASE
AND HERE COMES GARCIA!

01:19:55.997 --> 01:19:58.332
[ Groans ]

01:19:58.333 --> 01:20:02.420
WHOA!  GARCIA MAKES
A SPECTACULAR SAVE TO END THE INNING.

01:20:02.420 --> 01:20:05.339
WITH THE ANGELS BEHIND 2-0,
CLARK'S REALLY STRUGGLING.

01:20:05.340 --> 01:20:08.259
AND WITH ONE OUT IN THE TOP
OF THE FIFTH...

01:20:08.259 --> 01:20:11.178
AND A MAN ON FIRST AND SECOND,
BEASLEY COMES TO BAT.

01:20:11.763 --> 01:20:14.098
ANYBODY GOT ANY,
UH... YOU KNOW?

01:20:16.434 --> 01:20:19.353
[ Crowd Chattering ]

01:20:19.354 --> 01:20:24.609
NO QUESTION HE'S TIRING,
WALLY, AND KNOX KNOWS IT. BALL ONE.

01:20:24.609 --> 01:20:28.112
YOU 38HAD TO EXPECT THIS.
THEY'RE GETTING TILLER UP NOW IN THE BULLPEN.

01:20:28.113 --> 01:20:32.784
[ Sniffs, Coughs ]

01:20:32.784 --> 01:20:35.703
[ Groans ]

01:20:35.704 --> 01:20:39.207
[ Wilder ]  OH, MITCHELL
MAKES A GREAT PLAY... YEAH!

01:20:39.207 --> 01:20:41.542
- <i>AND GETS THE FORCE AT THIRD.</i>
<i>- ALL RIGHT!  ALL RIGHT!</i>

01:20:41.543 --> 01:20:44.462
ALL RIGHT!  ALL RIGHT!
GO, BABY, COME ON!

01:20:45.046 --> 01:20:48.549
[ Wilder ]  HERE IN THE SIXTH,
GARCIA'S ON FIRST WITH A SINGLE AS THE ANGELS...

01:20:48.550 --> 01:20:51.469
TRY TO BATTLE THEIR WAY BACK
INTO THE BALL GAME.

01:20:51.469 --> 01:20:54.388
THAT BRINGS UP
RAY MITCHELL.

01:20:54.389 --> 01:20:58.476
RAY'S BEEN HOT AS WILD FIRE
THE SECOND HALF OF THIS MIRACULOUS SEASON--

01:20:58.476 --> 01:21:03.147
BUT, AS MANY OF YOU KNOW, IN THE
PAST MITCHELL HAS CHOKED WHEN IT CAME TO PRESSURE SITUATIONS.

01:21:03.148 --> 01:21:07.235
YOU GOT THIS ONE, RAY!
YOU HEAR ME? YOU CAN DO IT!

01:21:14.826 --> 01:21:17.745
[ Wilder ]
MITCHELL CONNECTS!

01:21:17.746 --> 01:21:21.249
- <i>IT'S HIT DEEP!</i>
<i>- GO!  GO!  GO!</i> <i>GO!  GO!</i>

01:21:21.249 --> 01:21:23.584
- <i>[ Wilder ]  AND IT'S GONE!</i>
<i>-</i> <i>[ Crowd Cheers Hysterically ]</i>

01:21:23.585 --> 01:21:27.088
- <i>RAY MITCHELL HAS JUST HIT...</i>
<i>- ALL RIGHT!  YEAH!</i>

01:21:27.088 --> 01:21:30.591
A MONSTER HOME RUN
WITH A MAN ON TO TIE THE GAME HERE IN THE SIXTH.

01:21:31.176 --> 01:21:34.095
HEY!  WHOO!
ALL RIGHT!

01:21:37.015 --> 01:21:38.766
[ Cheering Continues ]

01:21:41.686 --> 01:21:44.605
[ Laughing, Cheering ]

01:21:44.606 --> 01:21:48.109
DON'T YOU STOP!

01:21:48.109 --> 01:21:51.028
[ Wilder ]
CLARK HAS HIS BACK TO THE WALL HERE IN THE SEVENTH...

01:21:51.029 --> 01:21:53.948
AS THE SOX ARE THREATENING AGAIN
WITH TWO MEN ON BASE.

01:21:53.948 --> 01:21:55.699
OKAY, WE'RE
HOLDING OUR OWN.

01:21:55.700 --> 01:21:59.203
HOLDING OUR OWN.
HOLDING OUR OWN.  GO! HANG IN THERE!

01:21:59.204 --> 01:22:01.539
[ Wilder ]
CLARK DEFINITELY COULD USE AN ANGEL NOW...

01:22:01.539 --> 01:22:04.458
AS HE'S TIRING
LATE IN THE GAME.

01:22:06.795 --> 01:22:10.298
[ Crowd Cheering,
Cheering Gets Louder ] [ Groans ]

01:22:10.298 --> 01:22:13.217
YEAH!  YEAH.

01:22:13.802 --> 01:22:16.721
[ Wally ]
THERE SEEMS TO BE SOME SORT OF MAGIC...

01:22:16.721 --> 01:22:19.056
IN THE WAY HIS TEAM
IS SUPPORTING HIM, RANCH.

01:22:19.057 --> 01:22:21.392
[ Man ]
LET'S GO, GUYS!  COME ON!

01:22:21.392 --> 01:22:24.895
HEY, KID.
HOW YOU DOIN'? FINE.  AL!

01:22:24.896 --> 01:22:28.983
HEY, KIDDO, SHARP OUTFIT.
I WISH I HAD ONE. THANKS.

01:22:28.983 --> 01:22:32.486
GEE, Ií AM GLAD TO SEE YOU.
YOU KNOW, I WAS AFRAID YOU GUYS...

01:22:32.487 --> 01:22:35.990
WOULDN'T SHOW UP TODAY SINCE,
YOU KNOW, A LOT OF PEOPLE KNOW ABOUT THE ANGELS NOW.

01:22:35.990 --> 01:22:38.325
NO ONE'S COMING.

01:22:38.326 --> 01:22:41.829
CHAMPIONSHIPS HAVE
TO BE WON ON THEIR OWN. IT'S A RULE.

01:22:41.830 --> 01:22:45.333
OH.  WELL, THEN,
WHAT ARE YOU DOING HERE?

01:22:45.917 --> 01:22:47.668
I CAME HERE
TO CHECK ON MEL.

01:22:47.669 --> 01:22:50.004
HE'S COMIN' UP SOON.

01:22:50.004 --> 01:22:52.923
- HE'S GONNA BE ONE OF US.
- Y-YOU MEAN HE'S--

01:22:52.924 --> 01:22:56.427
AH, HE SMOKED FOR YEARS.
IT'S ALWAYS A MISTAKE.

01:22:56.427 --> 01:22:59.346
<i>HE'S GOT</i>
<i>SIX MONTHS LEFT.</i>

01:22:59.931 --> 01:23:02.850
DOESN'T KNOW
ANYTHING'S WRONG YET.

01:23:02.851 --> 01:23:06.354
NO.
DON'T YOU WORRY.

01:23:06.354 --> 01:23:11.609
HE'S WELL TAKEN CARE OF.
YOU CONCENTRATE ON YOUR OWN LIFE NOW.

01:23:11.609 --> 01:23:13.944
WE EXPECT
GREAT THINGS FROM YOU, KID.

01:23:13.945 --> 01:23:17.448
WE'LL ALL BE WATCHING.
YOU REMEMBER THAT.

01:23:17.448 --> 01:23:21.535
EVEN THOUGH
YOU CAN'T SEE US, WE'RE ALWAYS WATCHING.

01:23:29.127 --> 01:23:33.214
[ Crowd Cheering ]

01:23:36.134 --> 01:23:39.053
<i>[ Spectators ]</i>
<i>COME ON,</i> <i>ANGELS!</i>             <i>ANGELS!</i>

01:23:39.053 --> 01:23:41.388
[ Wilder ]
WITH A MAN ON AND ONE OUT IN THE EIGHTH,

01:23:41.389 --> 01:23:44.308
CLARK IS SHOWING
DEFINITE SIGNS OF FATIGUE...

01:23:44.309 --> 01:23:47.812
AS HE PITCHES TO MARCH.
COME ON, MARCH. PUT IT HERE, MAN.

01:23:47.812 --> 01:23:51.899
- [ Wilder ]  BALL THREE.
- [ Crowd Groans ]

01:23:51.900 --> 01:23:55.987
[ Man ]  TAKE YOUR TIME, CLARK.
<i>[ Man ]</i> <i>GET READY TO GO, GUYS!</i>

01:23:55.987 --> 01:23:58.906
+.
EASY, MEL.

01:24:03.578 --> 01:24:05.913
[ Wilder ]  HERE'S THE PITCH.
AND MARCH GROUNDS TO MARTINEZ.

01:24:05.914 --> 01:24:09.417
THEY GET DARREN AT SECOND.
GARCIA THROWS.  DOUBLE PLAY!

01:24:09.417 --> 01:24:11.752
- YEAH!
- YEAH!  YEAH!

01:24:11.753 --> 01:24:17.008
[ Wilder ]
AND ONCE AGAIN, SOLID DEFENSE BAILS CLARK OUT OF A JAM!

01:24:17.008 --> 01:24:18.759
[ Laughing ]
HOW'D YOU LIKE THAT, COACH?

01:24:18.760 --> 01:24:21.679
OH, WAY TO GO!
WAY TO GO!  HEY!

01:24:21.679 --> 01:24:24.598
[ Wilder ]
IT'S STILL TIED UP HERE IN THE BOTTOM OF THE EIGHTH,

01:24:24.599 --> 01:24:30.438
BUT THE ANGELS HAVE GARCIA
AT BAT AND MARTINEZ ON THIRD WITH THE GO-AHEAD RUN.

01:24:30.438 --> 01:24:33.941
MARTINEZ GOES ON THE PITCH.
GARCIA BUNTS!

01:24:33.942 --> 01:24:36.861
AND IT'S A SQUEEZE PLAY!
HERE'S THE THROW.

01:24:36.861 --> 01:24:42.116
- MARTINEZ SCORES!
AND THE ANGELS TAKE THE LEAD! - [ Cheering ]

01:24:42.116 --> 01:24:45.619
- YEAH!
- [ Crowd Cheering ]

01:24:45.620 --> 01:24:48.539
YEAH!

01:24:51.459 --> 01:24:54.378
YEAH!
ALL RIGHT!

01:25:03.137 --> 01:25:04.888
[ Grunts ]

01:25:04.889 --> 01:25:08.976
[ Wilder ]
MESSMER POPS OUT TO GABOYAN TO END THE INNING.

01:25:08.977 --> 01:25:13.648
SO AS WE ENTER THE NINTH,
THE ANGELS ARE ONLY THREE OUTS AWAY FROM THE PENNANT...

01:25:13.648 --> 01:25:16.567
IF THEY CAN JUST HOLD ON
TO THIS 3-2 LEAD.

01:25:16.567 --> 01:25:19.486
HEY, MEL.
[ Boy ]  HEY, MEL, YOU'RE MY DAD'S FAVORITE PLAYER!

01:25:19.487 --> 01:25:21.238
LET'S FINISH THIS.
WE GOT 'EM.

01:25:21.239 --> 01:25:23.574
ALL RIGHT.
ALL RIGHT, THREE OUTS, BOYS.

01:25:23.574 --> 01:25:25.909
LET'S DO IT!
[ Wilder ]  SO WITH THE CHAMPIONSHIP ON THE LINE,

01:25:25.910 --> 01:25:28.829
MANAGER GEORGE KNOX ELECTS
TO SEND A TIRED MEL CLARK...

01:25:28.830 --> 01:25:32.333
OUT TO FACE THE HEART
OF THE WHITE SOX LINEUP.

01:25:32.333 --> 01:25:36.420
- HE'S ALL ALONE.
- <i>[ Man ]  LET'S GO.</i> <i>COME ON, ANGELS.</i>

01:25:37.005 --> 01:25:38.756
[ Crowd Cheering ]

01:25:38.756 --> 01:25:42.843
DON'T WORRY.
HE'LL GET AN ANGEL. MEL ALWAYS GETS AN ANGEL.

01:25:48.683 --> 01:25:53.354
[ Wilder ]
CLARK TAKES THE SIGN FOR HIS FIRST PITCH TO GASPER.

01:25:53.354 --> 01:25:55.105
LET'S SEE
IF HE HAS ANYTHING LEFT.

01:25:55.106 --> 01:25:58.609
GASPER GETS
A PIECE OF IT!

01:26:00.361 --> 01:26:05.616
AND IT FALLS IN FOR A SINGLE!
THE TYING RUN IS NOW ON FIRST.

01:26:10.288 --> 01:26:13.207
[ Sighs ]

01:26:16.127 --> 01:26:19.630
- ALL RIGHT.
- [ Phone Rings ]

01:26:19.630 --> 01:26:22.549
WE NEED SANFORD.
GET HIM READY. [ Sighs ]

01:26:26.054 --> 01:26:30.141
[ Wilder ]
THEY'RE GETTING SANFORD UP IN THE BULLPEN.

01:26:30.141 --> 01:26:34.228
[ Coughing, Sniffs ]

01:26:37.732 --> 01:26:40.651
- [ Grunts ]
- <i>[ Wilder ]  HE BUNTS!</i>

01:26:40.651 --> 01:26:43.570
CLARK FIELDS IT CLEANLY
AND GETS THE RUNNER AT FIRST,

01:26:43.571 --> 01:26:48.242
- BUT GASPER ADVANCES
TO SECOND ON THE SACRIFICE. - ALL RIGHT!  ONE DOWN!

01:26:48.242 --> 01:26:53.497
[ Wilder ]  WHITE SOX NOW
HAVE THE TYING RUN IN SCORING POSITION WITH DARREN AT BAT.

01:26:57.001 --> 01:27:00.504
- [ Cracking ]
- <i>IT'S IN THE HOLE!</i> <i>GARCIA DIVES!  HE GETS IT!</i>

01:27:00.505 --> 01:27:03.424
THE THROW IS OFF-BALANCE.
NOT IN TIME!

01:27:03.424 --> 01:27:05.759
SAFE!
HE'S SAFE. ARE YOU SURE?

01:27:05.760 --> 01:27:11.599
GASPER IS HELD ON SECOND,
BUT THE GO-AHEAD RUN IS NOW ON FIRST WITH ONLY ONE AWAY.

01:27:11.599 --> 01:27:15.102
[ Crowd Booing ]

01:27:18.022 --> 01:27:21.525
[ Man Yelling ]
HEY, KNOX, WAKE ;@UP!

01:27:21.526 --> 01:27:25.613
[ Wilder ]
CLARK LOOKS VERY TIRED.

01:27:25.613 --> 01:27:30.284
- [ Grunts ]
- <i>GABOYAN SWINGS AND SMASHES IT</i> <i>DEEP TO LEFT CENTER!</i>

01:27:30.284 --> 01:27:34.371
THIS IS TROUBLE!  WILLIAMS
GOT A GOOD JUMP ON THE BALL!

01:27:36.124 --> 01:27:39.043
- SOMEBODY BETTER TAKE CHARGE!
- [ Williams ]  I GOT IT!

01:27:41.379 --> 01:27:44.882
- <i>[ Crowd Cheering ]</i>
<i>- AND BEN WILLIAMS</i> <i>SAVES THE GAME FOR NOW...</i>

01:27:44.882 --> 01:27:48.385
- WITH A SPECTACULAR CATCH!
- [ Wally ]  AND A GREAT THROW TO HOLD THE RUNNER AT THIRD.

01:27:48.386 --> 01:27:51.305
TRY IT!

01:28:06.487 --> 01:28:12.326
[ Wilder ]
OH!  AND HE HITS BIRCH IN THE BACK ON THE FIRST PITCH.

01:28:12.326 --> 01:28:14.661
THAT LOADS THE BASES.

01:28:14.662 --> 01:28:19.333
AND KESEY, THE LEAGUE
R.B.I. LEADER, IS UP NEXT.

01:28:19.333 --> 01:28:25.172
[ Announcer ]
NUMBER 32, KIT "HIT OR DIE" KESEY.

01:28:33.931 --> 01:28:37.434
[ Wilder ]
I CAN'T BELIEVE HE'S LEAVING CLARK IN THE GAME.

01:28:37.435 --> 01:28:39.186
ANY HIT SCORES A RUN.

01:28:39.770 --> 01:28:44.441
THERE'S AN ANGEL
THERE NOW, RIGHT? NO.

01:28:48.529 --> 01:28:51.448
[ Wilder ]
THE RUNNERS TAKE THEIR LEADS.

01:28:56.704 --> 01:28:59.623
AND KESEY GOT A GOOD PIECE
OF THAT ONE, BUT IT'S FOUL.

01:28:59.624 --> 01:29:04.295
- WE'VE GOT ONE STRIKE.
- [ Sighs ]

01:29:07.798 --> 01:29:13.053
SANFORD IS READY
IN THE BULLPEN.

01:29:27.068 --> 01:29:29.987
- BALL ONE!
- <i>[ Wally ]</i> <i>HIS ARM HAS TO BE TIRED.</i>

01:29:29.987 --> 01:29:32.906
HE'S THROWN 156 PITCHES.

01:29:32.907 --> 01:29:36.994
<i>[ Crowd Cheering ]</i>
<i>[ Exhales ]</i>

01:29:45.753 --> 01:29:48.672
- BALL TWO!
- THERE'S ONE COMING, RIGHT, ROGER?

01:29:49.257 --> 01:29:53.344
I DON'T KNOW, J.P.
I--  I DON'T THINK SO.

01:29:55.680 --> 01:29:58.015
[ Grunts ]

01:29:58.015 --> 01:30:02.686
AND CLARK JUST
MISSES NICKING KESEY AND THE COUNT GOES TO 3 AND 1.

01:30:03.271 --> 01:30:06.190
HE'S WAY BEHIND
THE BATTER NOW. [ Sighing ]

01:30:06.190 --> 01:30:10.861
ANY ANGELS?
NO.

01:30:15.533 --> 01:30:19.036
- [ Grunts ]
- [ Cracking ]

01:30:19.036 --> 01:30:23.123
[ Wilder ]
AND KESEY JUMPS ON IT! THIS COULD BE THE GAME!

01:30:23.124 --> 01:30:24.875
IT'S DEEP!
IT'S DOWN THE LINE!

01:30:24.875 --> 01:30:28.328
IF IT STAYS FAIR,
IT'S OUTTA HERE!

01:30:28.796 --> 01:30:31.131
-[ Wally ]  IT'S GONNA BE CLOSE.
-FOUL, FOUL, FOUL!

01:30:31.132 --> 01:30:34.051
[ Wilder ]
BUT IT'S FOUL.

01:30:34.051 --> 01:30:36.970
X%
IT COMES DOWN TO A FULL COUNT. TWO OUTS, THE TOP OF THE NINTH.

01:30:36.971 --> 01:30:40.474
THE ANGELS LEAD BY ONE RUN,
AND FOR MEL CLARK,

01:30:40.474 --> 01:30:43.393
THIS IS
THE PRESSURE COOKER!

01:30:43.394 --> 01:30:48.982
I GOTTA TAKE HIM OUT.
[ Sighs ]  NO. PLEASE, JUST LET HIM TRY.

01:30:48.983 --> 01:30:51.902
HE'S ALL USED UP.
HE CAN'T DO IT BY HIMSELF.

01:30:51.902 --> 01:30:53.653
YES, HE CAN.

01:30:53.654 --> 01:30:57.741
ALL HE HAS TO DO
IS BELIEVE.

01:30:58.909 --> 01:31:01.244
[ Sighs ]

01:31:12.923 --> 01:31:17.010
[ Whispering ]

01:31:28.105 --> 01:31:30.440
[ Wilder ]
AND KNOX WILL PULL MEL CLARK.

01:31:30.441 --> 01:31:35.696
ALL I CAN SAY IS,
IT'S ABOUT TIME.

01:31:36.864 --> 01:31:41.535
- [ Sighs ]
- [ Sniffles ]

01:31:47.375 --> 01:31:49.710
I GOT NOTHING LEFT.

01:31:49.710 --> 01:31:53.213
YEAH, YOU DO.
YOU GOT ONE STRIKE LEFT.

01:31:53.214 --> 01:31:55.549
[ Sighs ]

01:32:03.140 --> 01:32:06.059
YOU GOT AN ANGEL
WITH YOU RIGHT NOW.

01:32:06.060 --> 01:32:08.979
JUST GOT HERE
AND HE'S GONNA HELP.

01:32:27.081 --> 01:32:32.336
KID SEES AN ANGEL?
YEAH, HE MUST. THAT'S THE SIGNAL.

01:33:12.626 --> 01:33:14.961
COULD HAPPEN.

01:33:44.742 --> 01:33:46.493
OKAY.

01:33:46.494 --> 01:33:48.829
[ Chuckles ]

01:33:48.829 --> 01:33:50.580
GO GET HIM
FOR THE CHAMPIONSHIP.

01:33:50.581 --> 01:33:53.500
[ Crowd Cheering ]
ALL RIGHT!

01:33:53.501 --> 01:33:55.836
COME ON!
YES! COME ON, MEL!

01:33:55.836 --> 01:33:57.587
COME ON, MEL!
HE STILL HAS IT!

01:33:57.588 --> 01:33:59.339
[ Wilder ]
LADIES AND GENTLEMEN, I DON'T BELIEVE IT,

01:33:59.924 --> 01:34:02.843
KNOX WILL LET CLARK STAY IN
TO PITCH TO KESEY.

01:34:02.843 --> 01:34:07.514
THIS IS NOT SMART BASEBALL.
THIS IS RIDICULOUS--

01:34:11.602 --> 01:34:14.521
[ Cheering ]

01:34:14.522 --> 01:34:17.441
LET'S GO, MY BROTHER.
COME ON.

01:35:01.819 --> 01:35:06.490
[ Grunts, Gasps ]

01:35:09.994 --> 01:35:12.329
[ Knox Screaming ]

01:35:12.329 --> 01:35:15.248
[ Wilder ]
HE'S GOT IT AND IT'S OVER! HE'S GOT IT!

01:35:15.833 --> 01:35:19.920
- I CAN'T BELIEVE IT!
- [ Wally ]  THE ANGELS WIN THE PENNANT!  WE WON!

01:35:19.920 --> 01:35:24.007
ALL RIGHT, J.P.!
WE WON, WE WON! YEA!  YEAH!

01:35:24.008 --> 01:35:26.343
[ Roger Laughing,
Screaming ]

01:35:26.343 --> 01:35:30.430
THERE <i>ARE</i> ANGELS!
NOT THIS TIME, MEL. YOU DID IT YOURSELF!

01:35:30.431 --> 01:35:32.182
[ Both Laughing ]

01:35:32.182 --> 01:35:35.101
WE WON!
WE WON! YEAH!

01:35:35.686 --> 01:35:39.773
[ Cheering, Shouting ]

01:35:39.773 --> 01:35:44.444
[ Crowd Roaring ]

01:35:44.445 --> 01:35:47.364
[ Laughing ]

01:35:47.364 --> 01:35:51.451
YEAH!  YEAH!
WE WON!

01:35:51.452 --> 01:35:54.371
ALL RIGHT!
[ Laughing ] YEAH!

01:35:54.371 --> 01:35:56.122
WHOO!
YEAH!

01:35:56.123 --> 01:35:59.626
[ Laughing ]
I CAN'T BELIEVE IT!

01:36:00.210 --> 01:36:02.545
RANCH.

01:36:02.546 --> 01:36:05.465
- YOU'RE FIRED.
- YOU CAN'T FIRE ME!

01:36:05.466 --> 01:36:07.801
I GOT A CONTRACT!

01:36:07.801 --> 01:36:10.136
I'M RANCH WILDER!

01:36:10.137 --> 01:36:14.224
EASY, RANCH.
LESS IS MORE.

01:36:14.224 --> 01:36:16.559
AND THE ANGELS
HAVE WON IT!

01:36:16.560 --> 01:36:21.815
[ Crowd Cheering Wildly ]

01:36:26.487 --> 01:36:29.406
[ Roger ]
MAGGIE!  MAGGIE!  WE WON! <i>MAGGIE!</i>

01:36:31.742 --> 01:36:33.493
WE WON!
WE WON!

01:36:33.494 --> 01:36:37.581
I KNOW.  I HEARD.
OH, CONGRATULATIONS. THE ANGELS WON THE PENNANT!

01:36:37.581 --> 01:36:41.668
[ Maggie ]
IT'S GREAT!  WELL DONE!

01:36:42.252 --> 01:36:46.923
- <i>OH, ROGER,</i>
<i>YOUR SOCIAL WORKER CALLED.</i> <i>- SHE DID?</i>

01:36:48.092 --> 01:36:51.595
- [ J.P. ]  WHAT THEY WANT?
- WAS IT ABOUT MY FATHER?

01:36:52.179 --> 01:36:55.682
- NO, BUT IT IS ABOUT
FINDING YOU A PERMANENT HOME. - [ Crying ]

01:36:55.683 --> 01:36:58.018
OH, J.P., COME BACK.

01:36:58.018 --> 01:37:02.105
J.P., COME BACK!
[ Door Slams ]

01:37:05.609 --> 01:37:11.448
YOU KNOW,
NOTHING'S PROBABLY EVER AS GOOD AS YOUR REAL PARENTS.

01:37:11.448 --> 01:37:16.119
BUT THERE'S SOME PEOPLE
WHO COULD CARE FOR YOU...

01:37:16.120 --> 01:37:18.455
AND LOVE YOU
AND TAKE CARE OF YOU.

01:37:18.455 --> 01:37:22.542
YEAH.
I GUESS SO.

01:37:22.543 --> 01:37:26.046
YEAH.

01:37:27.798 --> 01:37:31.885
ROGER, THE PERSON
WHO CALLED SOCIAL SERVICE,

01:37:31.885 --> 01:37:34.220
THAT WAS ME.

01:37:34.221 --> 01:37:37.724
I WANT TO TRY
AND BE YOUR DAD.

01:37:37.725 --> 01:37:40.060
I WANT YOU TO COME
AND LIVE AT MY HOUSE.

01:37:40.644 --> 01:37:43.563
YOU WANT--
YOU WANT--

01:37:45.315 --> 01:37:48.234
<
YOU OKAY, HONEY?

01:37:51.155 --> 01:37:53.490
NO WAY.
I-I CAN'T.

01:37:55.242 --> 01:37:57.577
YOU KNOW,
I CAN'T LEAVE J.P.

01:37:58.746 --> 01:38:02.249
I CAN NEVER LEAVE J.P.
HE'S COMING TOO.

01:38:02.249 --> 01:38:04.584
- HE IS?
- I HEARD THAT.

01:38:04.585 --> 01:38:06.920
[ Knox Laughing ]

01:38:06.920 --> 01:38:09.255
YEAH!

01:38:13.927 --> 01:38:16.262
WAIT,
WHAT ABOUT MAGGIE? <i>NO.</i>

01:38:16.847 --> 01:38:19.766
MY WORK IS HERE.
DON'T WORRY.

01:38:19.767 --> 01:38:22.686
<i>THERE ARE PLENTY</i>
<i>OF LITTLE ANGELS</i> <i>LOOKING FOR A HOME.</i>

01:38:22.686 --> 01:38:27.941
SO--  SO WE'RE
GONNA BE A FAMILY. YEP.

01:38:27.941 --> 01:38:31.444
I'M GONNA HAVE
A DADDY. [ Laughing ]

01:38:35.532 --> 01:38:38.451
I KNEW IT COULD HAPPEN.

01:38:38.452 --> 01:38:41.955
[ All Laughing ]

01:38:51.298 --> 01:38:54.217
WE'RE ALWAYS WATCHING.

01:38:58.889 --> 01:39:01.808
[ Bat Cracking,
Crowd Roaring ]

01:39:01.809 --> 01:39:06.446
♪ [ "Take Me Out
To The Ball Game" ]

01:39:06.446 --> 01:39:09.949
[ Crowd Roaring ]

01:39:09.950 --> 01:39:25.131
<i>♪</i>
